    <Placemark>
        <name>[Member-led] Understanding Online Surveillance for Everyday People</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>[Member-led] Understanding Online Surveillance for Everyday People</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Avondale Tap<br>3634 W Belmont Ave<br>Chicago, IL 60618</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Chicago Northwest</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Data privacy doesn&apos;t stop after the protest is over. Learn the basics of how to protect your every day data privacy at this event! No matter your experience level, we&apos;ll teach you the following basics:

1. How to minimize data leakage from your phone and laptop.
2. Why each privacy protecting step is important.
3. We&apos;ll show how each step works behind the scenes.

With a special focus on hindering ICE Surveillance, we&apos;ll make sure you and your neighbors are equipped to deal with the ever changing Digital Landscape.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/894961/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
