    <Placemark>
        <name>Support ICE Free Gurnee at Village Board Meeting!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Support ICE Free Gurnee at Village Board Meeting!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 3, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Gurnee Village Hall<br>325 O&apos;Plaine Rd<br>Gurnee, IL 60031</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> NE Lake County IL Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Support a Gurnee ICE Free Zone!

In the last year, Waukegan, Lake Bluff, and North Chicago have established ICE free zones, and Lake County also prohibits ICE on any county-owned property. After last year&apos;s incident at Warren Township High School, we hosted a Peace Walk in support of the children, educators, and families living in fear of ICE. Many courageous individuals have already been speaking up at Village of Gurnee Board Meetings, and we have recently heard from multiple Village Trustees that they would support the establishment of ICE free zones. It is time to take those efforts to the next level, and all speak up as one to say ICE OUT. 

**EVENT DETAILS**

We are asking all concerned residents of Lake County to pack the Village of Gurnee board meeting in an overwhelming show of support. If you live, work, shop, or own a business in Gurnee, we also ask that you make your voice known by giving a public statement in support of an ICE free zone. You are allotted up to 3 minutes to share why this is important to you and the rest of our community. 

STATEMENT RECOMMENDATIONS

We recommend you keep your comments polite and focused on the concern at hand. We know that our governing bodies respond better to messages around why a municipality benefits from such an action, rather than threats. While messages of hate surround us, we are committed to remaining peaceful and clear in saying ICE OUT. If you want more information about what to include, we also encourage you to attend our NELC-I General Meeting the Thursday before to get more tips and info! https://www.mobilize.us/nelakecountyilindivisible/event/899844

If you cannot attend, you can email your comments to the mayor and board at mayor@village.gurnee.il.us and villageboard@village.gurnee.il.us.

Even if you are not speaking, wear visible signs of support if possible - whatever you have that speaks to this cause is great. This is a grassroots effort organized by two amazing community members from Gurnee - they deserve us to all show up and support!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/907438/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
