        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Monona Defends the Constitution and Democracy</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Corner of Nichols Road and Monona Drive<br>Nichols Road &amp; Monona Drive<br>Monona, WI 53716</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>MONONA PROTESTS. MONONA DEFENDS THE CONSTITUTION AND DEMOCRACY

Saturday, February 14. 10:00 – 11:00. Nichols Road and Monona Drive.

Also February 28.

We the People Are Pissed! Resistance is growing. 

Protests are growing. The Giant is rising. Peacefully, non-violently, but with determination.

We the People are the Giant.  We are not going away.

More and more people across the country are telling the Trump regime that they don’t like what is happening to  the country. 

We don’t like ICE in our communities. We want ICE reined in. 

We really don’t like seeing families and communities ripped apart by anonymous masked ICE agents violently shooting, killing, arresting and detaining US citizens and immigrants with no criminal records. 

We are pissed that this authoritarian regime threatens to unilaterally take possession of Greenland, undermining NATO and our European allies. 

We are pissed that the regime uses overt, blatant, active racism to attack and divide us.

People  are tired of cruelty, and  lies, and chaos. This is no way to govern.

We are tired of the attacks on the rule of law.

People know that this is not what the United States is. Our laws, customs, values, and traditions are being ripped apart.  We object. We want No Kings!

When we protest, it gives others  courage to join us. They know they are not alone.

Join us! In Honor of Renee Good and Alex Pretti

**A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. We recommend all participants review our safety and security resource before your event: https://indivisi.org/safety**</p>
