        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No War, No ICE, No Kings Protest on Madison&apos;s East Side</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>3077 E Wash Av Frontage Rd<br>Madison, WI 53714</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> WisDems</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Meet us on Madison&apos;s East Side to Protest the Trump Administration.

This administration has deployed their secret police to our streets to abduct our neighbors and drive fear into the populace. We will not stand for ICE terrorizing our communities and murdering protesters. We demand an end to the terror and justice for all harmed. 

Trump&apos;s assault on Venezuela is an extreme abuse of power that cannot be tolerated. His actions could destabilize South America and cause widespread immiseration in the Western Hemisphere. How dare he do this in our name! We say, No! NO ICE! No war for oil! No to colonialism! We demand Peace among nations, peace in our communities, and the restoration of sanity.

We will be on the Starkweather Creek Path pedestrian bridge over East Washington Ave.  Please park on E Wash Av Frontage Rd at the dead end. It&apos;s an easy walk from there to the bridge. This is a non-violent protest. Bring your big signs and flags.</p>
