<h3>Knit for the Resistence</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Gardd Parc Condominiums<br>6767 Frank Lloyd Wright Ave<br>Middleton, WI 53562</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> WisDems</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Do You Knit? Show Your Resistance!

### Calling all Middleton Area Knitters! Come together and join the Resistance against ICE and the Authoritarian Regime&apos;s immigration policies.

Knit a Red Resistance hat as a symbol of immigrant rights and support hope and freedom for all.

We hope to make this a regularly recurring event. Bring your knitting supplies and we&apos;ll organize. 

Because of this project there is a shortage of red yarn. If you have extra please bring it.

### See the history behind this hat [here](https://www.npr.org/2026/01/31/nx-s1-5693767/red-hat-protest-minnesota)</p>
