        <name>No Kings III</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No Kings III</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Boone County Circuit Court<br>310 Courthouse Sq<br>Lebanon, IN 46052</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Boone County Resistance Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join  us for the third national day of action - NO KINGS III.   Bring your signs and voices to Boone County  Courthouse on 28 March, Noon to 2PM.   We  will have speakers, chanting, and will showing the world that Boone County, Indiana will not accept Kings.  Or fascists.  Or Nazis by any other name.    We will amplify our message together with groups all across America.   There may be a short march around the Courthouse.  There may be singing.  There may be costumes.  Bring something to keep you hydrated.  Wear your favorite Resistance T-shirt or inflatable!    

No Kings!  No Nazis!  No KKK!  No ICE.

A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

Indivisible prohibits carrying or bringing any weapon to an Indivisible event, whether or not the person is licensed to carry a firearm or weapon.

 Weapons include all guns, knives and other items that may be considered dangerous or that could cause harm. If a volunteer or member shows up at an Indivisible event with a weapon, the individual will be requested to leave.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/907801/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
