        <name>Craftivism Red Hat Resistance Knitting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Craftivism Red Hat Resistance Knitting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Warren County Democratic Party Headquarters<br>1231 Columbus Ave<br>Lebanon, OH 45036</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Warren County Democratic Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**&quot;MELT THE ICE&quot; hat**

If you are a knitter, this is for YOU!

While there was a history of Red Hat Resistance even before the NAZI era,
during the 1940&apos;s to protest the Nazi occupation of their country, the
Norwegians made and wore a red pointed hat with a tassel... a form of visual
protest. It is time for us to show our resistance! 

Let&apos;s get started on our **Knitted RESISTANCE HAT**

The materials you will need:

- Yarn- Red- 200 yards- DK weight
- Knitting needle size US6, US8
- Tapestry needle
- Scissors
- Stitch Markers

The pattern is on **[Ravelry](www.ravelry.com)** - there are several. 
One pattern option:
&quot;Melt the ice&quot; by Paul Neary *@Yarn_Cult* &amp; *@needlesandskein*


📅 Sunday, March 1, 2026
📅 Sunday, March 15, 2026

⏰2:00 pm - 4:00 pm 

📍Warren County Democratic Headquarters: 1231 Columbus Ave, Lebanon</p>
