        <name>We Are Not Expendable: Ice Storm Impacts, One Year On</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>We Are Not Expendable: Ice Storm Impacts, One Year On</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Treetops Resort<br>3962 Wilkinson Rd<br>Gaylord, MI 49735</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Climate Action Campaign</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for our Northern Michigan People’s Hearing–a community forum to bring a spotlight to the impacts and insufficient response to last year’s devastating ice storms. Free food will be available and the first 50 people to arrive will receive a free drink.

It’s been one year since the March ice storms that damaged communities in Northern Michigan. Many are still repairing their homes and rebuilding their livelihoods. All the while being expected to prepare for more extreme weather storms that are only getting worse due to climate change. FEMA denied our recovery, but our voices won’t be silenced.

Northern Michigan is not expendable, and our leaders need to hear that. This People’s Hearing is a platform for the community to share what they’ve lived through and speak directly with government representatives about what their communities need moving forward.

Join community members, local leaders, and environmental experts from across Northern Michigan to help elevate our voices and call on our elected leaders to fight for the community.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/887955/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
