        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Community Defense Network Training - LSURJ/KFTC</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 16, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Kentuckians For The Commonwealth</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Our communities are under threat from ICE, and we need to prepare to take care of each other including our immigrant neighbors.  Join Louisville Showing up for Racial Justice (LSURJ) and Kentuckians For The Commonwealth (KFTC) to learn Community Defense skills such as De-escalation, Know Your Rights, Accompaniment, Solidarity, and How Our Liberation is Connected to the Liberation of Others. 

With these skills, we can build teams to respond to calls for accompaniment - to challenge ICE and more. We are serving at vulnerable gatherings, meet ups, centers that accompany directly impacted communities, doing court accompaniment and more.   

This is a statewide training for KFTC members to think about putting together a CDN where they live.</p>
