        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stop the Cruelty, Columbus</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 2, 2026 at 9:30 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>395 E Broad St<br>Columbus, OH 43215</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Central Ohio</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This protest is at 395 E. Broad St, across the street from the intersection of Cleveland and Broad. There is parking in the area.  

Please note that this is not an ICE facility; it&apos;s an immigration and customs office.  We protest there to take advantage of rush hour traffic and do so after the office is closed so that we won&apos;t frighten people away from their appointments.

We provide the signs, which have red lettering on a white background and say, “Stop the Cruelty.” We all use the same sign to maximize visual impact. We are a silent protest, although we do talk among ourselves. We have a policy of not hassling ICE officers who wander by. Anger and resentment are Donald Trump&apos;s tools, they&apos;re not ours. Everyone is welcome!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/877865/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
