    <Placemark>
        <name>Copy of: NO KINGS III SIGN MAKING PARTY – WEST SIDE [Indivisible NEO/See U Next 2sday]</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Copy of: NO KINGS III SIGN MAKING PARTY – WEST SIDE [Indivisible NEO/See U Next 2sday]</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 14, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Rocky River Public Library<br>1600 Hampton Rd<br>Rocky River, OH 44116</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible NEO</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>No Kings III Day is March 28 — and we’re getting ready.

Join us on the west side for a high-energy Sign Making Party focused on creating bold, creative, powerful visuals for No Kings III Day.

Whether you’re a seasoned craftivist or picking up a marker for the first time, you are welcome here.

We’ll provide supplies (while they last), but it’s very helpful if you bring:
- Poster board or sturdy cardboard
- 5-gallon paint stir sticks (great sign handles — often free at Home Depot or Lowe’s)
- Extras of these materials to donate if you’re able


Special Activity: Reusable Upcycled Signs

This activity shows you how to turn old plastic yard signs into reusable protest signs with interchangeable messages. Instead of making a new sign every time, you’ll create one base sign that allows you to wipe off or change your message for each event.

We will provide yard signs to upcycle (while supplies last).

If you have old yard signs laying around at home that you’d like to reuse, bring them — this is a great way to give them new life and keep them out of the landfill.

If you’d like to create a reusable, message-swapping sign, consider bringing:
- Adhesive whiteboard covering material (example: https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DSFRF34L)
- OR adhesive chalkboard covering material (example: https://www.amazon.com/Borskyn-Chalkboard-Wallpaper-Blackboard-1-5ft-x32-8ft/dp/B0FHQPLRKC/ref=sr_1_28)

We’ll teach you how to apply it and create a sign you can reuse for No Kings III and future actions.


Additional Creative Activities Include:
- Making decorations for No Kings Day stage backdrop
- Decorating No Kings I.C.E. Whistles
- Assembling I.C.E. Whistle Packs
- Decorating No Kings Sashes
- No Kings Day Banner Making
- Crown Decorating
- Selfie Booth


About See U Next 2sday

See U Next 2sday is a Northeast Ohio–based arts activism group focused on making creative civic action more accessible. We believe creativity is a powerful tool for public engagement, education, and collective action — and that you don’t need to be an artist to participate.

If you’d like to support our work:
- Make a contribution at: buymeacoffee.com/see.u.next.2sday
- Or view our supply wishlist at: amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/2RM92Z0M04H4Q

We respect that many people are choosing not to purchase from Amazon. You’re welcome to use the list for ideas and purchase items from your preferred alternative store instead. Just email us at donate@next2sday.com to coordinate delivery or drop-off.

Every contribution helps us continue hosting free creative civic events like this one.


About Indivisible NEO

Indivisible NEO is a grassroots organization serving Northeast Ohio, mobilizing locally and advocating nationally to protect democracy and advance equity and justice.
To learn more or get involved, visit: indivisibleneo.org.


ADDRESS, TIME &amp; ADDITIONAL INFO

Saturday, March 14 | 1:00–4:00 PM
Rocky River Public Library
1600 Hampton Road, Rocky River, OH 44116

Hosted by See U Next 2sday (Indivisible NEO’s Art Activism Committee) + Indivisible NEO

[East Side option: Join us Saturday, March 7 at the Warrensville Heights Branch of Cuyahoga County Public Library in Warrensville Heights.]</p>
