    <Placemark>
        <name>NO KINGS 3 Twin Cities</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS 3 Twin Cities</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Minnesota State Capitol<br>75 Rev Dr Martin Luther King Jr Boulevard.<br>Saint Paul, MN 55155</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Twin Cities</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.

The Minnesota No Kings coalition of Indivisible Twin Cities, MN AFL-CIO, MN 50501 and Women&apos;s March Minnesota, is proud to be working with the national No Kings coalition to host the flagship No Kings 3 event on March 28th!

This event will highlight the amazing efforts of the people of the state and of the Twin Cities as we resisted Operation Metro Surge by saying loudly ICE Out of Minnesota!

What began in 2025 as a single day of defiance has become a sustained national resistance to tyranny, spreading from small towns to city centers and across every community determined to defend democracy. Our peaceful movement is bigger than ever.

This event will be a day of healing for those who’ve seen violence, A day of celebration for the lives of those we’ve lost. A day of peace for those who’ve done war, And a day of happiness, despite all of the attempts to break us.

Yes, of course this is about Democracy. It’s about the Country we live in, and the Land that we love. But it is also something more.

No Kings 3 is how we; average people, show the World a Path Forward. One that can be kinder, gentler. One that can be happier, and brighter. A Path that can be more JUST for those who walk it, and one where our neighbors, no matter who they are, can FEEL SAFE AGAIN.

Minnesota would like to share our secret with you, right now.

Join us for a march and rally at the Minnesota State Capitol. Marches will kick off at 12 noon, with the rally following at 2:00 PM CST. March gathering locations to be announced.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it.

A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/905314/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#exact</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
            <Data name="EventID"><value>905314</value></Data>
            <Data name="Organization"><value>Indivisible Twin Cities</value></Data>
            <Data name="LocationType"><value>exact</value></Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
            <coordinates>-93.1019519,44.9551923,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Constitutional Observer Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Constitutional Observer Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>White Bear Lake United Methodist Church<br>1851 Birch St<br>White Bear Lake, MN 55110</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> St. Croix Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ICE has descended upon the Twin Cities and surrounding areas, with thousands of masked agents terrorizing our region. They are tearing apart families, violating the civil rights of both immigrants and native-born citizens, and committing horrific acts of violence. Now they claim they will be backing down, but we have reason to be skeptical. Even if they do leave the Twin Cities, some ICE officers will remain, and others may simply move to the suburbs and rural areas.

Our communities are standing strong in solidarity against ICE’s assaults. There are already many people and groups responding to raids and documenting ICE activity. We are exposing ICE’s brutal tactics and helping to prevent abductions, but we need more people who are ready to respond.

In this training, you will learn to become a Constitutional Observer: how to document ICE actions, report and respond to ICE raids, assert your rights as an observer, get alerts, help families that are targeted, and more. Take this course and be on the right side of history!

The training will begin at 6:00 and run slightly more than one hour. Afterward, there will be plenty of time for Q&amp;A.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904273/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
