        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Borderland Documentary - Minnesota Immigrant Movement Fundraiser</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 3, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Main Cinema<br>115 SE Main St<br>Minneapolis, MN 55414</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Minnesota DFL</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We are helping Minnesota Immigrant Movement (MIM) with a fundraiser to help Minnesota immigrant families offset the expenses they are suffering following the ICE occupation in Minnesota. 

Movie Director Pamela Yates and Producer Paco de Onis will be introducing this extraordinary documentary by Zoom and will join us for a Q&amp;A following the film.

We are so very appreciative for your support for this special showing. ALL DONATIONS ARE FULLY TAX DEDUCTIBLE.

Several local Artists will be conducting a Silent Auction of their arts and crafts.

Prepared and paid for by 55th Senate District DFL, sd55dfl.org.</p>
