        <name>ICE OUT OF MN - Golden Valley/Crystal Bridge Brigade</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE OUT OF MN - Golden Valley/Crystal Bridge Brigade</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Hwy 100 Pedestrian Bridge<br>2450 Lilac Dr N<br>Golden Valley, MN 55422</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On Wednesday, January 7th, an American citizen, Renee Nicole Good, was killed by Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) in Minneapolis, Minnesota. On Saturday, January 24th, another American citizen, Alex Pretti was tackled and killed by multiple ICE agents in Minneapolis. This killing is part of a broader pattern of unchecked violence and abuse carried out by federal immigration enforcement agencies against members of our communities.

Since then, ICE has only escalated in abducting, harassing, and terrorizing our immigrant friends, family, and neighbors throughout MN. They break laws without abandon. They violate our constitutional rights. And we need to continue to speak out and raise awareness of their atrocities.

This event is to continue to build solidarity in resistance to ICE&apos;s actions, and connect community members with resources to help us through this invasion. Join us in telling ICE to leave MN for Good!

We will gather at the pedestrian bridge over Highway 100 in Golden Valley with our protest signs in a show of solidarity and resistance against the current ICE occupation of our state. This is to increase visibility and awareness that we want ICE OUT of MN.

A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/893371/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
