        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Signs of Solidarity: Plymouth Community Poster Making</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 14, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Plymouth Library - Hennepin County Library<br>15700 36th Ave N<br>Plymouth, MN 55446</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We will be gathering at the Plymouth library on Saturday, March 14 from 2 to 4 PM in the Vicksburg room to make signs in preparation for the No Kings protests on March 28th! 

Bring supplies or use ours! We will have loads of Minnesota themed whistles to give away. 

For those who knit or crochet, bring your gear and make the Melt the Ice hat with your community members! The pattern can be found on Ravelry, sold by Needle and Skein’s Paul Neary (a Minneapolis store). They are donating all the proceeds from this $5 pattern to the immigrant community!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
