        <name>National Day of Lobbying</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>National Day of Lobbying</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 9, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 4:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>431 W Main St<br>Tupelo, MS 38804</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This a local Indivisible event!
On 2.17, constituents from across all 50 states went into at least 110 in-district offices of US Representatives to talk about impeaching Trump and abolishing ICE. Some offices locked their doors and appeared visibly shaken (e.g., Nancy Mace); others sat down and had tough conversations with constituents. Across most offices – a common theme emerged: we don’t want to have to see you and have this discussion again.

So, on Monday, March 9th  – we’re going back! Impeachment is not optional. It is the remedy mandated by the Constitution. Likewise, Congress holds the power to de-fund and abolish ICE. They aren’t acting because they do not have the political will to do so. So we will lend them some more of ours. 
This day of action will be nonviolent, lawful, and constitutional. This is a coordinated civic action calling for constitutional accountability. It is an exercise of our first amendment rights to free speech, freedom of assembly and the freedom to petition our government for redress of grievances.  
This day of action will be nonviolent, lawful, and constitutional. This is a coordinated civic action calling for constitutional accountability. It is an exercise of our first amendment rights to free speech, freedom of assembly and the freedom to petition our government for redress of grievances.  



*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909626/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
