        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out for Good — Vote, Then Assemble</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Law Enforcement Detention Center<br>201 N Church St<br>Winston-Salem, NC 27101</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Camel City United Indivisible North Carolina</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On the final day of early voting, we are coming together for a county-wide action to make our voices heard.

First, we vote.
Then, at 4:00 PM, we exercise our First Amendment right to assemble.

We will gather at the Forsyth County Jail to make a clear public statement:

We want ICE out of our communities.

We do not want local law enforcement accusing, detaining, or cooperating with ICE beyond what the law requires.

Our communities deserve safety, dignity, and accountability — not fear.

This action is about visibility, presence, and people power.

We are calling people neighborhood by neighborhood —
from apartment communities to cul-de-sacs,
from churches to block groups —
to show up together and fill the space.

This is not about disruption.
It is about public accountability.
It is about being seen and counted.

Voting is how we use our ballots.
Assembling is how we use our voices.

Vote by 3.
Assemble at 4.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/893425/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
