    <Placemark>
        <name>Weekly Protest for an End to ICE in Cherokee County</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Weekly Protest for an End to ICE in Cherokee County</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 3, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Intersection of Main Street &amp; Hwy 92<br><br>Woodstock, GA 30188</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Cherokee United</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**ICE enforcement is expanding in plain sight and in silence.**

Across the country—and here in Georgia—ICE operations rely on racial profiling, secrecy, and fear. People are detained without notice. Families are separated. Children are taken from caregivers. Communities are left in the dark while their neighbors disappear from workplaces, homes, and schools.

**This is not about safety.**

**This is about power exercised without accountability.**

When government agencies operate without transparency, targeting vulnerable people while shielding their actions from public scrutiny, democracy erodes at the local level first. What happens to immigrant communities today becomes the blueprint for broader abuse tomorrow.

That’s why we show up. Every week. Together.

** We gather to demand:** 

• No ICE presence in our neighborhoods

• An end to racial profiling and secret enforcement actions

• Transparency, accountability, and community consent

• Public safety rooted in trust—not fear

———

**📍 Intersection of Hwy 92 &amp; Main St, Woodstock, GA**

**🕓 Every Tuesday • 4–5 PM**

**📣 Indivisible Cherokee United – Activism &amp; Mobilization**

_This is a nonviolent, community-centered protest. We organize peacefully._</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/872571/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
