<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Red River United Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On Friday, Feb 27, we are standing in solidarity with the students, their families, and staff of Moorhead High School who may be impacted by the recent ICE activity in Minnesota. We will be standing on both sides of 21st St. South in front of the High School, as well as the corner of 21 St. S. and 4th Ave. S, from 3:00 pm - 4:30 pm. As always, our attendees are reminded of our expectations that we are peaceful, non-violent and free from alcohol, drug, and weapons. Signage should be positive and supportive with language such as We Love Our Immigrant Neighbors; No One is Illegal on Stolen Land; or Ice Out. Signs in Spanish would also be welcomed.</p>
