        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Bridge of Truth &amp; Hope- Cherokee &amp; I20</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Bridge of Truth &amp; Hope- Cherokee &amp; I20</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 1:30 PM UTC - 3:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Cherokee Ave. Overpass at I-20<br>410 Cherokee Ave SE<br>Atlanta, GA 30312</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible ATL</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Our message this week will touch on ICE’s planned detention centers in Georgia and
why supporting funding for ICE without guardrails in place is detrimental to democracy.


TRUTH: Sometimes there is more truth in a simple message like NO KINGS. Especially when we are overloaded with all the conflicting information that is out there, and even more so with so much disinformation.

Hope: It is easy to feel alienated and disheartened. Our presence on the overpasses seems to be a way to reconnect and encourage each other. We can see it on the faces of people (and we can see many) who drive by, and when they wave and give a thumbs up. And we can surely hear it in the honking, and messages of thanks. Maybe our wave is our greatest gift.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/875333/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
