        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Indivisible Event Safety 102: Know Your Rights Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:15 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Lancaster Together</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Know Your Rights Training

The whole world is watching Minneapolis and many of us are asking: what do we do if ICE comes to our community? Join us to hear from Matt Johnson about your Constitutional rights during ICE enforcement and how to keep our whole community safe.

Unchecked and unlawful actions by federal DHS employees remind us that citizens need to know their rights in order to speak out with confidence. Attend this training with one of our local experts so you can understand better what you can do, and be in a position to share that information with others. 

Let&apos;s all take care of ourselves and each other!</p>
