        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Sign Wave Saturdays - Rte 213 &amp; Spring Ave Chestertown</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Maryland 213 &amp; Spring Avenue<br>Chestertown, MD 21620</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us every Saturday, 11-12 for peaceful sign waving on the sidewalks. Bring a sign! Bring a friend!

#ICE OUT NOW
From Maryland to Minnesota, we’re joining together by the thousands to demand an end to this regime’s assault by eliminating ICE from our communities. It’s time to free our cities of masked militia. Free our friends and neighbors from abductions and concentration camps. And free America from this regime of the bullies, for the billionaires. 

This cowardly regime and its masked militia are assaulting families, invading homes, kidnapping children, and murdering people on the street. We must eliminate ICE and bring agents and the people giving them their orders to justice.

To truly make America the land of the free, we must ensure it remains the home of the brave – the brave of us who have moved heaven and earth to make a new life, faced assault by the cowardly masked ICE militia, and now continue to demand dignity, justice and freedom even from within this regime’s concentration camps.  

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
