        <name>Protest Citizens Bank: Round 2</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Protest Citizens Bank: Round 2</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Public sidewalk<br>4345 Kirkwood Hwy<br>Wilmington, DE 19808</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Newark DE</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Indivisible Newark DE and Indivisible Highlands and Beyond for their second protest against Citizens Bank at the Kirkwood Highway location.

When banks fund ICE detention, they are not neutral — they are complicit. Citizens Bank is a major lender to companies that build and operate ICE detention centers, profiting from a system that cages and abuses immigrants. We are coming together to demand accountability and to make it clear: our communities will not accept banks fueling ICE abuse.

## Event Basics
- Saturday, March 7th
- Sidewalk outside the Citizens Bank at 4345 Kirkwood Highway

## Parking Info
- A firm representing the shopping plaza told us we can&apos;t park in the plaza (which is private property) during the protest, even if we intend to frequent one of the businesses while there. 
- See www.IndivisibleNewarkDE.org for a parking map

## Event Logistics

- ⭐ Rain or Shine • No March • Peaceful Protest⭐ 
- 🚫 No weapons, drugs or alcohol, please!
- 🦺 We have a team of volunteers to help ensure the event runs smoothly and safely.
- 🔲 Homemade signs are best.  If you are able, please make a sign to amplify the protest theme.

## Sign Ideas
- De-ICE Citizens Bank
- Defund ICE
- Cages Aren’t Communities
- Citizens Bank – Stop Financing ICE prisons
- Citizens Bank + ICE = Human Rights Abuse
- ICE Prisons Don’t Strengthen Our Communities
- Stop ICE
- No ICE Prisons
- Citizens Bank- Cut Ties With ICE Prisons
- Invest in People, not ICE Prisons</p>
