    <Placemark>
        <name>Stitching With Care</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stitching With Care</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 7:30 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Eastern Monroe Public Library<br>1002 PA-611<br>Stroudsburg, PA 18360</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Poconos</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Stitching with Care


Because community is built one stitch at a time.

 

In times of uncertainty, gathering together can be a powerful act of care.

 

Stitching with Care is a relaxed, welcoming space to knit, crochet, stitch, mend, or simply sit in good company. There is no formal agenda and no pressure — just hands at work and the kind of conversation that unfolds naturally when people share a table.

 

This is not a class or a structured lesson. However, experienced crafters are often happy to offer guidance if someone has a question. Bring a project you’re already working on, start something new, or simply come curious.

 

Our March 1 gathering at the Eastern Monroe Public Library will also include an opportunity to participate in the red “Melt the ICE Cap” project — inspired in part by the Norwegian resistance hats worn during the 1940s occupation, and more recently by knitters in Minnesota who reminded us that resistance can take many forms: singing in the streets, lighting luminaries on frozen lakes, riding bicycles through city neighborhoods — and yes, knitting red caps.

 

Participation in the cap project is entirely optional. You are welcome to work on your own project or simply enjoy the company. Please bring your own needles and hooks.


This is an experiment in building community the old-fashioned way — by showing up, sharing space, and creating something with our hands.

 

If it grows, it grows. If it simply becomes a good afternoon together, that’s enough too.

 

📍 Eastern Monroe Public Library

📅 March 1 2:30-4:00pm

🔗 Please RSVP to receive additional information.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909846/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
