        <name>Citizens Bank: Stop Funding ICE Prisons</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Citizens Bank: Stop Funding ICE Prisons</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 4:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>733 W Lancaster Ave<br>Bryn Mawr, PA 19010</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Upper Merion Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us Saturday, March 7, at 10 AM as we come together across Pennsylvania to send a message to Citizens Bank and raise awareness in our communities about Citizen’s role in supporting for-profit detention operators.

Citizens Financial Group, through subsidiaries like Citizens Bank, has long financed private prison and detention operators despite decades of allegations of abuse, neglect, forced labor, and fraud. Companies like CoreCivic and GEO Group have caused widespread harm — including wrongful deaths, medical neglect, and exploitation.

Right here in Pennsylvania, GEO operates the Moshannon Valley Processing Center, the largest ICE detention facility in the Northeast, just three hours from Montgomery County. Join us-- and others statewide-- to tell Citizens Bank that we want them to stop supporting cruelty.

A core principle behind our events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908469/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
