        <name>Unity in Action: Politics and Coffee Talk</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Unity in Action: Politics and Coffee Talk</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 3:30 PM UTC - 4:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Haddonfield United Methodist Church<br>29 Warwick Ave<br>Haddonfield, NJ 08033</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Cooper River Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>BREWING IDEAS TOGETHER 

SPECIAL GUEST: Deb, from CRI-Mutual Aid Team, will talk to us about the efforts their group is working on in 2026.

Join for conversation, community, and fresh ideas. Coffee and Politics Talk is the perfect space to connect with like-minded people, exchange experiences, and enjoy the finest coffee in town. 

Location: Haddonfield United Methodist Church, 29 Warwick Rd, Haddonfield

There is plenty of parking behind the church, and the main entrance is from the parking lot (not on Warwick Avenue). When you enter take the stairs to the immediate left to the basement. There is also an elevator.

Cooper River Indivisible is doing a food collection to support the families in Camden affected by ICE, plus the children in the school, who are also needed supplemental snacks. Please consider bringing a few of the items below to our next meeting:
Rice 	
Limes 	
