    <Placemark>
        <name>Indivisible Sussex March 10 Meeting</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Indivisible Sussex March 10 Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 10, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Sussex County Library - Sussex-Wantage Branch<br>69 County Rd 639<br>Wantage, NJ 07461</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This a local Indivisible event!

Earlier this month, one of our Indivisible Sussex friends posted a message on Heylo, “No way out but through. No way thru but together.” We have been thinking a lot about that message as we consider how our members are working together to support each other and our community. Appealing to our elected officials, rallying against ICE detention centers, providing support for the hungry, reaching out to youth, “singing” resistance, consuming as much history and civics as humanly possible, we are working our way out of this mess. We also consider this message as we move ahead and consider the most effective ways to sustain our activism–It must be together. 

Perhaps you read about “neighborism” in a recent Atlantic essay by Adam Serwer (Minnesota Proved MAGA Wrong). Serwer observed that the people of Minneapolis embraced an ethos of, “protecting the people around you, no matter who they are or where they came from.” He then noted, “The contrast with the philosophy guiding the Trump administration could not be more extreme.” What we are learning (or maybe we knew all along) is that successfully challenging this regime must come from the grassroots of our communities of ordinary people who strive to protect one another.

Our meeting conflicts with dinnertime and many people come hungry, so to fill our bellies and nourish our friends, we welcome you to bring a small plate of treats to share if you are interested and able. We still have lots of t-shirts and hats to distribute. We encourage you to invite a friend, family member, kindred spirit, or maybe anyone who is fed up with the disaster regime. Our tent is big and our community is welcoming!

Our giving opportunities this month are OSCAR Animal Rescue and we are collecting non-perishable items for a local food pantry.

Feel free to reach out with questions. If you’re not already signed up with our group, you can do so by heading over to IndivisibleSussex.org.

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909312/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
