        <name>Rapid Response Training  (CRNOK)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Rapid Response Training  (CRNOK)</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 9, 2026 at 11:30 PM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>3207 S Blvd<br>Edmond, OK 73013</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Edmond</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Indivisible Edmond is hosting CRNOK for a Rapid Response Training.

Immigration enforcement activity is increasing across Oklahoma, and our community needs to be prepared.

This Rapid Response and ICE Verification Training, led by Community Response Network Oklahoma (CRNOK), is designed to equip community members with the knowledge and tools to show up responsibly when it matters. Participants will learn about knowing their rights, recognizing enforcement activity, and responding safely and effectively during immigration emergencies.

This is about being prepared as a community so fear and confusion do not fill the gap when enforcement activity occurs.

Registration is required. No special experience required.

We are grateful to Southern Hills Christian Church for generously providing space for this training.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908490/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
