        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>March Monthly Meeting</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>BETHANY Library - Metropolitan Library System<br>6700 NW 35th St<br>Bethany, OK 73008</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible OKC</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>*NOTE LOCATION*

Join us for our Indivisible OKC monthly meeting on Saturday, March 7th, 1:00 PM at the **BETHANY** Library.

Guest Speaker: Community Response Network Oklahoma (CRNOK)
Community Rapid Response

This month, we’re hosting a Rapid Response Training with CRNOK – Community Response Network Oklahoma in response to the continuing immigration and ICE activity across our state.  

This rapid response and ICE verification training, led by CRN, is designed to educate and empower our community during this critical time. As Immigration and Customs Enforcement activity increases in Oklahoma City, our goal is to ensure everyone knows their rights, can identify enforcement actions, and respond safely and effectively to protect our undocumented neighbors.

**Registration is required.**

Whether you’re brand new or have been with us since day one, this is a great meeting to attend.</p>
