        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
            <coordinates>-75.1638758,38.3783275,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
    </Placemark>
    <Placemark>
        <name>Driscoll Foods Collaborates with ICE at Newark Schools, let&apos;s drop them!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Driscoll Foods Collaborates with ICE at Newark Schools, let&apos;s drop them!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 10:15 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Sir Isaac Newton Elementary School<br>150 Newton St<br>Newark, NJ 07103</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This will be our 2nd meeting that we are going to at the Public Newark Board of Education Meeting to protest Driscoll Foods.

Driscoll Foods is a family-owned, food supplier business based in NJ. They supply the food at Delaney Hall in Newark, the largest detention center in our state. They directly profit off of the separation of families and the actions of ICE in NJ.

They have a contract with Newark Board of Education as well and we are showing up to ask them to find a new food supplier. We will be hosting a rally outside the meeting before going in to put in our public comments.

We let them know in January&apos;s meeting that Driscoll collaborates with ICE. We need to ask them where they stand now that they know. 

Anyone who wants to speak at the meeting does need to register here, 5 days before the meeting. Please do so here:  https://www.nps.k12.nj.us/board-of-education/meetings/public-participation-request/  

Join us!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/891569/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
