    <Placemark>
        <name>General Membership Meeting - What the Flock?</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>General Membership Meeting - What the Flock?</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, March 12, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Guilderland Public Library<br>2228 Western Ave<br>Guilderland, NY 12084</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Guilderland Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>There&apos;s been a lot of buzz lately about Flock cameras, and we&apos;ve got a bunch right here in Guilderland. Come to our March general membership meeting to learn about Flock cameras, presented by our friends at Indivisible Albany. 

This will be a discussion about the widespread proliferation of Flock camera systems, including throughout the Capital District, as we launch our public education campaign about how Flocks work, where they are, how the data is retained and, more importantly, how this data is being funneled to federal agencies such as ICE to target and track immigrant communities. We will also discuss actions that you can take to fight back against the installation of Flock cameras and to demand accountability for those already in use. We think this will be an extremely informative session and we hope you can join us.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/906256/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
