    <Placemark>
        <name>Jersey City KYRs Outreach Walk - South Asian Communities</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Jersey City KYRs Outreach Walk - South Asian Communities</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br><br>Jersey City, NJ 07306</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> AAPI New Jersey</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join AAPI New Jersey to outreach to Desi &amp; Indo-Carribean communities in Jersey City about how to prepare for ICE in our communities. We will speak to community members, workers, business owners about what they are experiencing and share in-language Know Your Rights materials. 

If you are a resident of Jersey City and/or speak a South Asian language, please join us! This outreach walk is specifically for Jersey City community members. If you are not a resident of Jersey City, feel free to reach out and let us know what neighborhood you&apos;re based in and we can do our best to connect you with existing efforts in your area.

Exact location and meet-up details will be shared with those who confirm.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/906414/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
