        <name>Stronger than Fear: Solidarity Walk in Palisades Park</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stronger than Fear: Solidarity Walk in Palisades Park</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 3:30 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Broad Ave<br>Palisades Park, NJ 07650</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> AAPI New Jersey</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Together, we are stronger than fear! Please join AAPI NJ and Estamos Unidos for a solidarity walk to support immigrant-owned small businesses impacted by near-daily ICE activity in Palisades Park. With many community members feeling isolated and fearful, Broad Avenue, usually a bustling hub, has been quiet--creating hardship for its small businesses.

If you speak Korean or Spanish, help us talk with the business owners on Broad Avenue about what they&apos;ve been experiencing, their legal rights in encounters with ICE, and how they can protect their employees.

No language skills? No problem! You can help distribute Know Your Rights info and show support for these businesses by walking and shopping with us.

No cost to attend, but please bring funds to cover your purchases and RSVP for the meeting point. We&apos;ll start with a brief orientation. See you there!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908228/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
