        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Making Our Resistance Visible</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 8:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Corner of Green Grove Road and Asbury Avenue in front of the CVS<br><br>Tinton Falls, NJ 07753</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Come protest ICE, Trump, oligarchs, DOJ, Illegal Tariffs, Illegal war actions, and more. Keep vigil for those murdered and/or disappeared by ICE, chant “NO,” bring a sign (and an American flag) on any of the myriad topics that you want to send a message on—justice-fascism-politics for oil. Take a break to spend an hour with patriots who think like you! This is an event scheduled especially to give locals the opportunity to resist and protest peaceably and very visibly. All are welcome, even if you are not a local. When enough of us say “NO,” it will stop. Join us every Sunday from 2 to 3 PM at the corner of Green Grove Road and Asbury Avenue in Tinton Falls, NJ, on the sidewalk in front of the CVS.


Here is where you&apos;ll describe your local event. Please be specific about important details and include anything a first time attendee, or new group member, might find helpful!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
