        <name>North Country Immigrant Defense Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>North Country Immigrant Defense Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 2:30 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Crandall Public Library<br>251 Glen St<br>Glens Falls, NY 12801</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible ADK/Saratoga</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**Defending Our Neighbors. Protecting Our Community.**

**Fed Up With Injustice?** Do you feel frustrated knowing that ICE operates with a lack of due process? Do you want to learn how to help defend the rights of our immigrant neighbors and stop the criminalization of our communities?

Indivisible ADK/Saratoga and, our community partners, are hosting this critical Immigrant Defense Training in Glens Falls. As federal enforcement escalates, we are coming together to strengthen our unified, regional response.

This essential workshop will provide you with the tools and knowledge you need to fight back, including:  

&gt;**Know Your Rights (KYR) Training:** Learn what to do and what to say during an encounter with immigration enforcement to protect yourself and others.  

&gt;**Rapid Response Network:** &quot;Learn how to document federal activity, notify the community, and participate in an effective neighborhood response network.&quot; 

&gt;**Community Power:** Connect with organizers and volunteers from Saratoga, Washington, Warren, and Essex Counties to collectively strategize and plan for a sustainable defense.  

**Please Note:** Space is limited, first come first serve.  

 **CHOOSE YOUR TRAINING TRACK**

&gt;**TRACK 1**: Full Day Immersion Highly recommended for new volunteers or those looking for a refresher on both legal rights and rapid response tactics.

&gt;**TRACK 2**: Afternoon Only (ICE Rapid Response) Requirement: This option is reserved **ONLY** for individuals who have previously attended a formal &quot;Know Your Rights&quot; training.  **Come at 12:30pm.**

**BUILD COMMUNITY POWER**

*Indivisible ADK/Saratoga is a local chapter of [Indivisible](http://Indivisible.org), active in NY&apos;s Saratoga, Warren, and Washington counties, that welcomes people with our shared values and goals. We organize and mobilize for actions that safeguard and advocate for vulnerable communities, protect human rights, guard our planet, elect progressive candidates, and protect democracy. We are committed to non-violence as a guiding principle in everything we do.*

Find us online:

[Website](https://www.indivisibleadksaratoga.com)

[Bluesky](https://bsky.app/profile/indivisible-adk.bsky.social)

[Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/share/g/19myt9wGmE)

[Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/indivisibleadksaratoga/)

Email us: indivisibleadksaratoga@gmail.com</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908141/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
