        <name>Beacon Shine the Light Thursdays:  ICE Out for Good!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Beacon Shine the Light Thursdays:  ICE Out for Good!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 5:30 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Bond Street &amp; Grace Avenue<br>Great Neck Plaza, NY 11021</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This a local Indivisible event!

Join The Beacon for Thursday Shine the Light, as we bring our voices to the street every Thursday from 12:30-1:00 PM.

Each week, we make our voices heard wherever we are. As beacons, we shine light by making a sign and bringing it outside—in front of our houses, apartment buildings, to our street corners, subway stops, etc.

Our signs proudly share whatever we’re feeling in our souls in the face of this regime’s actions. Our signs might read, “I Stand With Our Immigrant Neighbors,” or “Honk if You Love Ukraine,” or “Trans Rights Are Human Rights,” or “Read Banned Books.” We encourage a POSITIVE message on all signs, and request that you do not use profanity.

In the face of increasing violence against people in Minneapolis and throughout the country by ICE agents, we stand together to express our disapproval of our government&apos;s brutality.

Together, we are building visible resistance and organized compassion, meeting our neighbors, and joining together in acts of solidarity. We find joy in resistance through community, music, comedy and street theater.

There are Beacon groups all over the USA. Our local Great Neck group meets every Thursday from 12:30-1:00 pm throughout the cold weather months.

For more information on the Beacon, visit www.beaconfordemocracy.org

Link to event information: https://www.tinyurl.com/thursdaylight


*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/891498/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
