        <name>KEEP ICE OFFICES OUT OF LONG ISLAND!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>KEEP ICE OFFICES OUT OF LONG ISLAND!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 9:30 PM UTC - 11:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>88 Froehlich Farm Blvd<br>Woodbury, NY 11797</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ICE is expanding across the USA.  They are leasing offices and building new facilities in almost every state, including NY.  

Per Wired Magazine, &quot; In Woodbury, New York, a hamlet in Long Island, ICE is moving into offices located at 88 Froehlich Farm Boulevard, near an expedited passport center.&quot;

We will not let this stand. 

Join us for 2 events! 

Friday, Feb 27th at 4:30 PM outside the main building to picket and show that ICE will not be welcome into Woodbury.

Please bring lots of noisemakers, signs, and get ready to march!

And Saturday, Feb 28th, from 1 pm to 3 PM which will be community resource focused!

*****SATURDAY: Please bring a non perishable food donation item for Eileen&apos;s Free Bodega*****


Hosted by United Voices for Freedom: Long Island and Assemble Long Island



*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
