        <name>NO KINGS Middlebury, Vermont</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Middlebury, Vermont</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>3 Main St<br>Middlebury, VT 05753</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**Join Indivisible Middlebury from 11 - 1 p.m. for a NO KINGS event at the Middlebury Town Green on Saturday, March 28, and let your voice be heard!**

Right now, the Trump administration wants us to feel afraid, isolated, and powerless. They divide people on purpose and hope we stay quiet. While families are dealing with rising costs and losing access to healthcare, this administration is giving more power to ICE, spreading fear in our communities, and chipping away at our democracy day by day.

They’re counting on us being exhausted or too scared to speak up. But we know better. Our strength comes from community, from showing up for each other and standing together.

America doesn’t belong to strongmen or billionaires. It belongs to the people.

**So come out on March 28. Join your neighbors. Let’s remind them what real power looks like: our voices, our solidarity, and all of us standing together!**

Bring signs.
Bring friends.
Bring your energy!

*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
