    <Placemark>
        <name>Congressional District 1 Candidate Forum</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Congressional District 1 Candidate Forum</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 24, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Otis S. Johnson, Ph.D. Cultural Arts Center<br>201 Montgomery St<br>Savannah, GA 31401</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Savannah Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Meet the Democratic candidates running for Georgia&apos;s 1st Congressional District. You&apos;ll learn about their viewpoints on the issues facing coastal Georgians right now:

- Cuts to healthcare, SNAP, and other benefits
- Destructive tariffs and rising unaffordability
- Attacks on the rights of women and the LGBTQIA+ community
- The unhinged domestic terrorism of ICE
- The climate crisis

And more! Hear where each candidate stands _and_ their proposals for fixing these problems.

With Earl &quot;Buddy&quot; Carter vacating his House of Representatives seat, _now_ is the time to flip this seat blue with a candidate that stands by the people of Georgia instead of another billionaire-first, Trump sycophant.

The program will start at 6 PM and will feature an opportunity for the audience to ask questions.

Parking is available at the Civic Center.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/895484/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
