<h3>Standout in Solidarity with Migrants</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Pride gas station<br>25 Russell St<br>Hadley, MA 01035</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Volunteers for Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Feeling ICE-solated? Come join a wonderful group of people in one of the longest running Resistance Standouts in the area. We joyfully meet each Saturday, 12-2, rain, snow, sleet or wind to celebrate our Solidarity with the most vulnerable members of our community. Park at Hadley Crossing or on Bay Road, not at Pride. There&apos;s a button to cross the street from Hadley Crossing. This event will also be part of No Kings 3 on March 28. We&apos;re hoping to line Rt.9 from Northampton to Amherst and beyond.</p>
