        <name>NO KINGS AMHERST</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS AMHERST</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Amherst Town Common<br>1 Main St<br>Amherst, MA 01002</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

What began in 2025 as a single day of defiance has become a sustained national resistance to tyranny, spreading from small towns to city centers and across every community determined to defend democracy. Our peaceful movement is bigger than ever.

When our families are under attack, and costs are pushing people to the brink, silence is not an option. We will defend ourselves and our communities against this administration’s unjust and cruel acts of violence.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.

## Rally and March-Downtown Amherst

### Program Schedule (could be subject to changes)
-	12:00 -12:30: Kickoff and Gathering at Kendrick Park
-	12:30 - 1:00: March down North Pleasant Street to Town Common
-	1:00 – 2:00 Rally with music and speakers at Amherst Town Common

### Event is rain or shine. 

### Bring your signs, flags, banners! 

NO KINGS IN AMERICA! 
HANDS OFF! 
WE THE PEOPLE!
ICE OUT FOR GOOD
DE-ICE America
Stop the Shakedown! 
We are Not For Sale!

### Event Guidelines
-	Attendees must commit to nonviolence.
-	No weapons, no illegal substances, no alcohol.
-	Attendees must agree to follow the direction of the event leaders and marshals.
-	Attendees should agree not to engage with counter-protesters (unless as marshals).
-	Attendees agree to NOT block pedestrians, sidewalks, streets, or entry to buildings.

This is a local Indivisible event, co-sponsored by Indivisible West Quabbin, the Amherst League of Women Voters, the Pelham Democratic Town Committee, and many other community groups. Check out our Event Program Guide for a full list of co-sponsors. Indivisible West Quabbin is a pro-democracy and social justice-committed grassroots group, grounded in the communities west of the Quabbin Reservoir: Amherst Area, Eastern Franklin County, and beyond!

### Program Details and Accessibility Notes
-	Plan ahead and expect limited parking [https://www.amherstma.gov/732/Parking-in-Amherst](Townof Amherst Parking Map)
-	For parking near Kendrick Park, there is a parking lot behind Primo Pizza and free parking at the Amherst Regional High School, located at 21 Mattoon Street. 
-	Porta-potties, including accessible porta-potties, will be on site at the Town Common but not at Kendrick Park. 
-	The march will be approximately .6 miles on level ground and will be coordinated by No Kings Event Marshals. 
-	See Welcome Tables on Town Common for event information and first aid. 

### Please consider purchasing from local businesses while you are visiting to support our local downtown businesses! 


### Co-Sponsors and Event Guide

Please click the link below to access our Program Guide, which includes everything you need to know about this amazing, peaceful event, including a schedule, map, and an up-to-date list of our coalition partners and co-sponsors. The Event Guide will be posted at least two weeks before the event and updated as needed. Go to [https://www.indivisiblewestquabbin.org/no-kings-amherst](NO KINGS AMHERST Event Page). 

For more information: indivisiblewestquabbin@gmail.com


*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/901586/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
