        <name>&quot;Be Ready&quot; Practice Session</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>&quot;Be Ready&quot; Practice Session</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Universalist Unitarian Congregation<br>47 Cherry St<br>Saint Johnsbury, VT 05819</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible St. Johnsbury</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Wonder how you might respond if a Trump supporter gets in your face?  What are the steps to follow if you see someone getting detained by ICE or some other apparent federal law enforcement?  What are effective ways to engage with people who are “on the fence” politically?

The *“Be Ready”* practice sessions give folks an opportunity to practice how to respond in difficult situations via role playing and reflective processing.  The sessions are held twice monthly, after every Wednesday Action Group meeting. We start around 12:10pm.

We meet upstairs in the sanctuary, accessible from the Cherry Street parking lot. Please park on the street or in the lot north of the building -- the lot at Eastern and Cherry is for another property. Please reserve the parking lot for those that need closer access.</p>
