        <name>De-Ice Citizens Bank</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>De-Ice Citizens Bank</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Citizens<br>4 Cocasset St<br>Foxborough, MA 02035</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Mansfield and Beyond</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Citizens Bank funds private prisons used in the regime&apos;s brutal, unconstitutional, illegal, anti-immigrant actions. Stand with us at this peaceful protest, to expose Citizens role in this, and to show our immigrant neighbors that we support them.

Suggested phrases for signs 
Citizens Bank: Stop Financing ICE prisons 
Citizens Bank: Cut Ties with ICE prisons 
Citizens Bank: Don&apos;t Bankroll ICE 
Citizens Bank: Get Out of ICE Business 
 Citizens Bank: Customers Want You Out of ICE 
De-ICE Citizens Bank

Finally, By attending this event, you are committing to:
nonviolence
bringing signs not weapons
ignoring disruptors
being part of the group as opposed to standing alone
paying attention to safety marshals (those wearing orange safety vests)
Allow only the safety leads to interact with law enforcement, if we are approached by them.


You participate at this event at your own risk.


We also suggest that you:


disable biometrics on your phone, like face and touch ID
do not livestream. 
video from a safe distance, with your phone locked. (We prefer that you not post videos of disruptors.)
listen to law enforcement officers and If you are videotaping them because of concerns, that you narrate what you&apos;re doing while videotaping.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899901/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
