        <name>Citizens Bank: Stop Financing ICE Prisons!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Citizens Bank: Stop Financing ICE Prisons!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Citizens Bank Harvard Sq<br>30 Brattle St<br>Cambridge, MA 02138</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Progressive Mass Cambridge</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The De-ICE Citizens Bank Coalition is doing it again!

Join others at dozens of Citizen Bank branches all across the northeast to send Citizens a clear message: financing private prison and immigration detention facility operators The GEO Group and CoreCivic is bad for business.

We&apos;ll stand out on the public sidewalks at Citizens Banks with signs and informational leaflets.  We will urge Citizens Bank customers to contact their local branch managers and relevant executives of the Bank about its investments in ICE and the possibility of closing their accounts. Non-customers can contact Citizens executives and spread the word.

Please bring only signs specific to this Citizens Bank action, such as: 
Citizens Bank: Stop Financing ICE Prisons! // ICE Cages Aren&apos;t “Communities” // “Strengthen Our Communities”? Not with ICE Prisons! // Citizens Bank: Cut Ties With ICE. 

We&apos;ll have a few extra signs. Bring US flags too!

Dress for the weather. Unless it is unsafe, we plan to be out in solidarity with activists around the country who don&apos;t let weather deter them! Bring hand/foot warmers if you need them. Sign Up to receive notice of any cancellation. 

BACKGROUND. Citizens Bank publicly presents itself as a community-centered institution committed to social responsibility. Yet the Bank continues to maintain key financial relationships with CoreCivic and The GEO Group, two notorious, for-profit, prison corporations that build and operate immigration detention facilities for ICE, provide transportation services to ICE, and operate prisons for mass incarceration. 

For more details about Citizens Bank’s relationship to the private prison system, go to boycottcitizens.org 

In response, the De-ICE Citizens Bank Coalition (de.ICE.CitizensBank@gmail.com), presently comprising progressive organizations from CT, DC, MA, NJ, NY, PA, RI, VA, and VT will hold coordinated standouts near Citizens Bank branches on Saturday, March 7, 2026. An interactive map of participating locations will be available here:  tinyurl.com/De-ICECitizensBank

THE ASK. The Coalition calls upon Citizens Bank to live up to its stated values by publicly committing to end its financial relationships with private prison and detention contractors as soon as legally possible. These actions are intended to send a clear message: corporations and financial institutions that enable harmful immigration and detention policies must be held accountable by the communities they claim to serve.

A core principle behind all of these events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events. Please do not block business entrances or traffic.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903872/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
