<h3>Community Defense: Supporting our Immigrant Neighbors</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 15, 2026 at 5:00 PM UTC - 7:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Aeronaut<br>14 Tyler Street<br>Somerville, MA 02143</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Somerville</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Indivisible Somerville for a training that will empower individuals to understand their legal rights as bystanders in an Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) encounter. 

This Community Defense Training is for anyone who wants to stand up to ICE and learn how to create a community that affirms the dignity of all its members, and especially our immigrant community members. Facilitated by a nationally-renowned trainer, political consultant, and community educator Elaine Almquist.

This event is at Aeronaut Brewery in Somerville, so participants must be 21 or older. Children can attend but they must join with their parents (who have to be over 21).</p>
