        <name>✊Standing Against ICE in Colorado with Michael Dougherty❌🧊</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>✊Standing Against ICE in Colorado with Michael Dougherty❌🧊</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>This is a special session of the weekly &quot;After We March, We Organize!&quot; Zoom call, hosted by Solidarity Warriors. To sign up for future calls, go to https://www.mobilize.us/solidaritywarriors/event/790061/

Boulder County District Attorney Michael Dougherty will give a presentation on Standing Against ICE in Colorado. The presentation will cover:

1. When was ICE formed, and for what purpose

2. What are the differences in authority between local law enforcement and ICE? Can an ICE agent legitimately order a US citizen out of their car?

3. What are the legitimate roles of an ICE agent?

4. How do the procedures of ICE differ from local law enforcement (training, do they de-escalate)?

5. What can we do in confrontations with ICE?

6. What specifically appeared to happen with the killings in Minneapolis?

7. How do CBP and ICE compare?

8. What is the situation with CBP and their practice of turning a vehicle into a weapon?

Join us to learn your rights and how to stand against ICE in Colorado.


*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908664/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
