<h3>Feb Community Gathering for Fremont County CO Indivisible</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Hive Canon City<br>729 Main St<br>Cañon City, CO 81212</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for the monthly Potluck Community Gathering to find out what we are doing, ways to get more involved, and meet more members of our community. 

After the quick update on our group, we will be learning how to knit the Melt The ICE red hat. A shop in Minneapolis has made a pattern for a hat inspired by a protest hat worn by Norwegians in the 1940s to resist the Nazis. This shop is using all proceeds to help immigrant families who have been harmed by ICE. 

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
