        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>March Monthly Meeting with Defend &amp; Recruit</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 3, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>St Mark Lutheran Church<br>1120 Curlew Rd<br>Dunedin, FL 34698</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible North Pinellas</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for our monthly meeting! Our mission is to model and promote grassroots engagement and participatory democracy and to ensure the values and interests of all are prioritized over corporate power and wealth. We are committed to social justice that honors and defends the rights of all.

**This month, we have a special presentation from Defend and Recruit. 

Trump&apos;s immigration crackdown is tearing communities apart.
He’s escalating raids, targeting immigrants, proudly separating families – even detaining U.S. citizens. His policies and ICE’s lawlessness has taken lives, devastated hundreds of thousands of people, and threaten millions more.

Learn about immigration defense campaigns and strategies to defend our people and build power in your community. This introduction training will cover the basics of immigration defense, including starting a neighborhood ICE watch,  building 4th Amendment Workplaces, winning municipal resolutions and legislation to support our communities and taking on corporations enabling ICE.

Join us for this informative introduction into building an ICE defense network. 

***REGISTRATION IS REQUIRED as seating is limited. There will be a Zoom option available. 

🚗Carpooling encouraged. Please park in the lot along the south side of the building adjacent to Curlew Road.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899513/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
