        <name>Stop 287g, Abolish ICE! Lakeland, FL</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stop 287g, Abolish ICE! Lakeland, FL</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 9:30 PM UTC - 11:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Lakeside Village Mall<br>1479 Town Center Dr<br>Lakeland, FL 33803</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p># 🛑 Stop 287g ⛓️‍💥 Abolish ICE 🧊 Save the Everglades 🐊
*Hosted by DEFUND OLIGARCHY · BLESSED BY LIBERTY · INDIVISIBLE*
([en español](https://mobilize.us/s/skrhfa))

#### Non-Partisan Public Demonstration — Saturday, Jan 24, 2026
##### Lakeland, FL

For 01/24, we are meeting at 4:00 pm at the intersection, but we will be more on the side in front of Starbucks and Louis Papa&apos;s, but outside the mall, not inside the mall. Locally this is a small assembly, but we are in solidarity with many other groups throughout the nation demonstrating against Avelo, 287g agreements, and human rights abuses in small cities just like ours.

##### Read all instructions

We are taking a stand for ICE abolition and against the removal of individuals without due process — violating the core principles of our republic. 

This is a call to action. We’re joining forces to demand that Polk County end its involvement in unconstitutional detention policies.

# 🪧 Our Demands
✊ Polk County Government, it’s ICE or us.

You cannot serve both the people and an agency that tears families apart, starves humans, withholds water, denies medical care, kills people, forces humans into slavery, performs sterilizations without consent, and refuses to recognize U.S. birth certificates and REAL ID.

✊ Polk County residents: Boycott anyone profiting from ICE

✊ Polk County: End 287g agreement.

✊ DHS &amp; James Uthmeier: No Alligator Alley Concentration Camp. No cages on sacred ground. 🐊

✊ ICE: Stay out of Florida. Stop terrorizing schools, hospitals, courthouses, and workplaces. End detention. Process only violent offenders with criminal convictions.

✊ LPD &amp; PCSO: Do not cooperate with ICE. Arrest ICE agents operating without signed judicial warrants for violent criminal offenders.

✊ Sheriff Grady Judd: Stop collaborating with ICE until DHS reforms are complete. PSCO should not be helping send people to concentration camps.

✊Scott Franklin, Rick Scott, Ashley Moody: Defund &amp; abolish ICE. 

✊ Florida State Legislature: Ban the use of state taxpayer money for ICE operations. Pass legislation banning cooperation with ICE beyond what federal law requires.


# 🛑 WHY WE’RE PROTESTING

❌U.S. citizens and work permit holders — like Juan Carlos Lopez-Gomez and Heidy Sanchez Tejeda — have been detained without cause.

❌DHS &amp; ICE have unilaterally seized protected land in the Everglades to create a 5,000-person prison with no A/C and no access to lawyers by raiding FEMA and charging the state $450 million, despite the objections of county and tribal leadership. 

❌Children are being separated from parents, denied legal representation, and even deported during active custody disputes — like two-year-old citizen known as V.M.L.

❌Our Constitutional rights — due process, legal counsel, protection from executive overreach — are being ignored.

# ✨ WE STAND FOR:
- Families
- Immigration rights
- Due process
- Constitutional liberty for all
- Holding corporations accountable for profiting from human suffering

# 🗓️ EVENT DETAILS

📍 Lakeland, FL 

🕒 Saturday, Jan 24, 2025, 4 pm - 6 pm

🎨 Signs provided (but feel free to bring your own especially if it highlights the case of individuals who have been unlawfully detained or removed)

🎭 Costumes, instruments &amp; kids welcome

🌞 Dress for the weather &amp; wear sunscreen, sunglasses, and a mask for privacy

🚶‍♀️ Accessible sidewalks

📢 We will be singing and chanting

🚻 Nearby public restrooms available

🚗 Free parking 

# 💡 TIPS

👍We are committed to nonviolence and having a peaceful assembly. Stay respectful in all interactions.

👍Be alert: impersonators and fake news outlets posing as independent media may be present. Verify credentials before giving an interview.

👍Don’t engage with trolls or agitators. They may pretend to be a fellow protester. If they are really interested, you can point them towards the pamphlets and literature that we have. Remember we are fighting for everyone&apos;s rights, even the people that don&apos;t agree with us and the ones that are really annoying.

👍Focus your energy on building unity and protecting our democratic, constitutional republic.

# 🎶 SING FOR LIBERTY 
### We recommend brushing up on these songs if you like to sing along, but we alternate a lot with regular chanting and mini speeches, so no pressure to sing.

- [This Land is Your Land](https://youtu.be/2Q7PULELvok?si=2ZBVKeoM5Ker0Zad)

- [My Country ’Tis of Thee](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xnH_OIgNgSY)

- [America the Beautiful](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWJF1yE3Y1E)

- [Star Spangled Banner](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fF01L85TYaw)

# 🔗 RSVP &amp; MORE INFO

✅ RSVP on Mobilize is optional

🌐 Event details will also be posted at www.blessedbyliberty.org 

📄 Learn more about Avelo’s ICE contract: www.stopavelo.org

#We stand together — and together, we will win.
#StopAveloLakelandFL #SayNoToAvelo #DefundOligarchy #DueProcessForAll #StopAvelo #BlessedByLiberty #IndivisibleLakeland #Indivisible #DefendTheConstitution #AgainstAllEnemies</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/792072/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
