    <Placemark>
        <name>Peaceful Rally and Food Drive</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Peaceful Rally and Food Drive</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 2:00 PM UTC - 5:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Palm Beach Boulevard &amp; Marsh Avenue<br>Fort Myers, FL 33905</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Democratic Party of Lee County</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Rally at the Palm Beach Blvd and Marsh Ave location for February 28th.  We will be collecting a lot of food, feminine hygiene, baby supplies, new clothes, and personal care items .  Start finding some BOGO deals right now, and save it up for the 28th.  All items donated go to local families identified by Lee County Schools.

 John (Cheesehead) has already assembled 40 Family Boxes of food in preparation for our Feb 28th Rally on Palm Beach Blvd at Marsh Ave in Fort Myers from 9-12.   

We are going to use this rally as another direct distribution event to that nearby community of folks who are afraid to leave home for fear of detention.  Ice, and our local law enforcement agencies working with/for them, has been stopping work vehicles along Palm Beach very frequently. Children remain inside their homes. School attendance is down.  Our Sheriff has asked for 10s of millions of dollars MORE from what ICE gives to our state so that his deputies can expand their detention efforts here. They are using drones to watch construction sites in our county. They can then easily nab workers as they come to the sites or prepare to leave after working in our blazing Florida sun all day. They are not slowing down, and neither are we in our efforts to feed as many children and innocent families as we can.

 
As part of the Direct Distribution event, we are asking people to bring food, perishable (yes produce, but not meat) and non-perishable food, new clothing, personal care items, baby items, feminine care items, TP, cleaning products, children’s books, toys, etc. to the Feb. 28th Rally on Palm Beach Blvd.
 

So what is in a “Family Box” you might ask. John described it as having something for every meal in it.  Harry Chapin also has a standard family box, which Lois Tome showed on her show recently (Google Lois Tome Family Box video), which they say feeds a family of 4 for 5 days.  Here is what Harry Chapin includes:

Oatmeal/Cereals/Cereal bars/Protein Bars 

Milk – shelf stable

Peanut butter and jelly

Juice

Mac &amp; Cheese

Tomato Pasta Sauce

Pasta

Rice 

Beans

Canned Tuna/Chicken/Pork

Canned Fruits/Applesauce

Canned Veggies

Canned soups – meal in a can type 

 
From our working with people in our communities recently, we have added/modified some things based on what they have asked for from us.  

 

 

Some of these other requested items are:

 

Oils

Spices

Corn Flour

Flour

Sugar

Chicken stock

Tortillas – corn &amp; flour

Snack Items

Drinks

And for the Feb 28th rally – please feel free to bring Produce and bakery items – no raw meats please, as we cannot keep it at a safe temperature.  I am thinking onions, potatoes, fruits, veggies, cilantro, breads, sweets…

 

We have volunteers who will help sort the food as you bring it on Feb. 28th. Of course, if you want to work on a family box, or many family boxes by yourself, or with friends/community, we would be thrilled to have those!  We can arrange for pickup – just email me - or you can bring them to the rally.  If you have a group in your community looking for a service project, please consider us!

 If you want to help with sorting and distributing food, clothes, and other items, bringing tables and tents, please let me know that too. It will be hot so we need all the help we can get!


Thanks so much to each of you who has participated in these events, in whatever way you can. You keep us going.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/907807/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
