        <name>Indivisible Wilton Manors - Resist Wilton Manors</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Indivisible Wilton Manors - Resist Wilton Manors</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 3:00 PM UTC - 4:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>5 Points Wilton Manors<br>2663 N Dixie Hwy<br>Wilton Manors, FL 33334</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**ICE out for GOOD! You showed up for Renee Good &amp; Alex Pretti! THANK YOU!!**
*Now Join Indivisible Wilton Manors with Resist Wilton Manors EVERY Saturday 10-11.30am at Five Points in Wilton Manors.* 
We have an ongoing food drive to support Poverello our local food pantry and a diaper drive to support Preggo organization for women. Bring your heart and your signs as we sing, dance, shout and let it all out! No one likes this authoritarian regime and we certainly do not agree to anyone&apos;s rights being taken away from them. Join us in the heart of our beautiful LGBTQIA+ city as we stand up for the constitution, due process &amp; justice for all, protecting our immigrant community from this administrations attempt to terrorize them, protecting women&apos;s rights and our families friends and neighbors. Be PROUD, show your COURAGE and stand OUT against this administration and all its hatred of those that may be different from them. Our rights are being eroded away in the LGBTQIA+ community. Our Trans sisters and brothers are being attacked. Our freedom to marry the person we love is being attacked. This ends with us all standing up and saying NO!!! We had a AMAZING turnout to our No Kings Oct 18th at Coral Ridge Mall &amp; the beach but that is just the beginning! You have seen us out on the streets now it&apos;s time for you to join us! Driving by? Honk your horn in support and make a plan to attend another music festival soon. Bring a sign, hat, sunscreen, water and some friends and family. It&apos;s time. Join us.

A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/878814/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
