<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Powered by People</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Are you serious about turning the tide in Texas? Are you tired of sitting on the sidelines and ready to make a difference? 

If you answered yes, then you have come to the right place!

Sign up here to join us in registering eligible attendees to the Student United Against ICE to vote!

10:45 am: Arrive to the venue

10:45 - 11 am: Volunteer training on Reach and prep for event

11 am - 1 pm: Register eligible attendees 

1 - 1:15 pm: Volunteer debrief and breakdown of setup

To register voters at this event, you MUST be a certified Volunteer Deputy Voter Registrar (VDVR) in at least EL PASO COUNTY (bonus points if you are also certified in the surrounding counties). Make sure your certification is current.

NON-VDR VOLUNTEERS WELCOME TO ASSIST WITH REGISTRATION CHECKS

**How to prepare:**

**STEP 1:** If this is your first time registering voters with Powered by People, please sign up below for a quick [Zoom training](https://www.mobilize.us/poweredxpeople/event/776672/).
OR if these times don&apos;t work for you, try our &quot;On Your Own Time&quot; Training: https://mobilize.us/s/8ckmRX</p>
