        <name>❌🧊 Community Action at City Hall: No ICE Detention in Surprise!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>❌🧊 Community Action at City Hall: No ICE Detention in Surprise!</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>16000 N Civic Center Plaza<br>Surprise, AZ 85374</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Northwest Valley Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Community Action at City Hall: No ICE Detention in Surprise!

Over **1000 people** have protested the proposed ICE detention facility in Surprise at previous city council meetings.

We MUST do it again.

**Surprise residents** are strongly encouraged to sign up to speak during public comment at the **Surprise City Council meeting on Tuesday, March 3rd at 6:00 PM**. Speakers should focus on what the City *can* do:

- Clarify their opposition to the proposed facility  
- Refuse voluntary cooperation with ICE  
- Initiate legal challenges and environmental reviews  
- Coordinate multi-jurisdictional opposition
- Demand federal accountability

We&apos;re done asking questions that DHS won&apos;t answer. Now we&apos;re making demands.

Sign up in advance to speak:  
https://surpriseaz-services.app.transform.civicplus.com/forms/24865

**Not a Surprise resident?**  
Join us for a **peaceful protest on the sidewalk outside City Hall** during the meeting. Your presence helps reinforce the message being delivered inside.

**Recommended sign:**  
**NO ICE IN SURPRISE!**

This is about sustained, visible community pressure.  
Show up. Speak out. Stay engaged.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908623/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
