        <name>Pathway to Power Victorville</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Pathway to Power Victorville</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Victorville City Hall<br>14343 Civic Dr<br>Victorville, CA 92392</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> California Working Families Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The High Desert has always been a region built by working families. For too long, local politics has happened to us instead of with us, but that changes now.

This is a moment to show that our community is paying attention, getting organized, and ready to build real local power.

Join us in Victorville as we rally alongside Working Families Party leaders and allies, including Stevonna Evans and Chris Ochoa, to stand with Derek Marshall and everyone fighting for safer streets, accountable leadership, and a future that works for working people.

This isn’t politics as usual. It’s community showing up for each other.

Come out. Bring your people. Let’s build something bigger together.

*This event is part of our Pathway to Power series, where WFP is laying out how people can come together to win governing power for the working class. In addition to what you&apos;ll hear from WFP, we are gathering to protest at the Victorville City Council against the council&apos;s attempt to remove Derek as Planning Commissioner for standing with students walking out against ICE&apos;s abuse of our communities.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/911026/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
