    <Placemark>
        <name>ESCONDIDO CITY COUNCIL: SPEAK OUT AGAINST ICE FIRING RANGE CONTRACT - FEB 25 at 5 PM</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ESCONDIDO CITY COUNCIL: SPEAK OUT AGAINST ICE FIRING RANGE CONTRACT - FEB 25 at 5 PM</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Escondido City Hall<br>201 N Broadway<br>Escondido, CA 92025</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible North County San Diego</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p># WHY THIS CITY COUNCIL MEETING IS IMPORTANT: 

Late last year, the Escondido Police Department quietly renewed a contract allowing ICE agents use of the city’s firing range. [See this LA Taco article](https://lataco.com/escondido-dhs-firing-range-contract) for a full background of the contract and decision:  

After significant pushback from the community, the Mayor agreed to place the ICE contract as an agenda item at the City Council meeting on Wednesday, February 25th. It is extremely important for EVERYONE to SPEAK OUT at this meeting to tell the Mayor and City Council that they need to cancel this contract immediately.

# WHAT YOU CAN DO: 

(1)  Attend the Wednesday, 2/25 City Council Session at 5 p.m.  To speak or register your position, fill out a yellow speaker card located at the front of the room, and place it in the basket near the City Clerk who sits on the far right of the dias. Volunteers will also be handing out speaker slips and they can help you. 

If you want to speak, fill in the agenda number (&quot;Information Session RE: EPD Firing Range Contract&quot;).

If you do not want to speak but just register your position, you can mark that on your speaker slip. 

This is the chance for Escondido and all County residents to show up and speak to Council urging them to cancel the contract. THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT THING YOU CAN DO TO ENCOURAGE COUNCIL TO IMMEDIATELY TERMINATE THE CONTRACT. For full details on the City&apos;s contract with DHS/ICE to use your city&apos;s firing range [click this link](   https://escondidoindivisible.org/cancel-ice-firing-range-contract-in-escondido/).

2 - Contact the Mayor, and City Council members, and demand that they cancel the contract with ICE.  [See this toolkit](https://docs.google.com/document/d/11bHBBRK43QUNw4geG99g7MrjqrjdKDfLZgayz-5X620/edit?tab=t.0) for all the relevant contact info.
 
A press conference starting at 4:00 PM at the Escondido City Hall will preceed the City Council session.

# SCHEDULE OF EVENTS: 

4:00 PM - Press Conference, with local community member speakers; 

4:30 PM – Head into City Council Chambers, fill out a yellow comment card up front. Bring your &quot;CANCEL THE CONTRACT&quot; and &quot;ICE OUT&quot; signs (no larger than 8&quot; x 11&quot; in size; we will also have some signs to borrow on-site); 

5:00 PM - City Council Session begins

After the unabated abductions, breaking up families, and terrorizing communities, including the killing of multiple people on the streets and in detention centers, it is unconscionable that the City of Escondido would continue working with this rogue agency. It is critical that we Stand Up, Speak Out, and demand that the Mayor and City Council CANCEL THE CONTRACT allowing ICE to use our city&apos;s firing range.  Let City Council know that # WE DO NOT WANT OR NEED ICE IN OUR COMMUNITIES! 

As always, peaceful protest and non-violent demonstration protocols apply. If you cannot commit to these, please do not attend.

# ADDRESS &amp; PARKING: 
201 N. Broadway, Escondido.  A large, free public parking lot for California Center for the Arts, Escondido and surrounding area events is located between Broadway &amp; Escondido Boulevard on Woodward Ave.  Follow the sidewalk through the park to the large fountain: council chambers are located on the northeast side (Broadway side) of the fountain.  There is also street parking on Broadway.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908238/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
