        <name>Whistle Kit Making Party with Indivisible Eastside - Redmond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Whistle Kit Making Party with Indivisible Eastside - Redmond</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 3, 2026 at 10:30 PM UTC - 12:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Together Center<br>16305 NE 87th St<br>Redmond, WA 98052</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Join Indivisible Eastside in blowing the whistle on ICE!

Whistle Kit making parties are a community safety practice rooted in resistance movements in LA and Chicago to help alert neighbors during immigration raids.

On **1st &amp; 3rd Tuesdays of the month** we get together to learn, build, connect, and strengthen our collective safety network. In moments like these, we’re reminded that __protection is not just a policy, it’s a community responsibility.__

The most important thing to bring is yourself! 

We are 100% grassroots, volunteer-led and funded. If you’d like to help us offset costs, we can accept online contributions at https://bit.ly/IE-Donate-W, or can provide an alternative method. *This event is free. No contribution is required.*

If you&apos;re unable to attend but would like to contribute materials, you can **drop whistles or kit supplies off at the [Together Center](https://togethercenter.org/$0) front desk, where we now have a whistle drop!** (16305 NE 87th Street, Redmond WA 98052)

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/877951/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
