        <name>ICE Out of Home Depot Mission Valley</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out of Home Depot Mission Valley</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 7:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Home Depot Fairmount<br>5920 Fairmount Ave<br>San Diego, CA 92120</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Us: NDLON Organized Community Action  

**Saturday, February 28**  
**Locations:** Home Depot stores across San Diego County  

San Diegans will take part in a coordinated, peaceful action at Home Depot stores throughout the county. Community members will gather outside their local Home Depot to raise signs and lift their voices in support of our neighbors who are under siege.  

During the action, a letter of demand will be delivered to store management. This collective action is about standing together, showing up for one another, and demonstrating the strength of community solidarity.

## Join us and make your voice count.

---

## Tips for Success

- Some signs will be available, but making and bringing your own is encouraged.  
- **Do NOT park in the Home Depot parking lot.** Please use street parking.  
- Meet on the public sidewalk across the street from the store.  
- Bring your joy and raise your signs and voices in support of our neighbors.  

Together, we show that our community stands united.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/906061/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
