        <name>IndivisibleCovingtonWA Whistle Workshop</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>IndivisibleCovingtonWA Whistle Workshop</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Kent Education Association Office<br>10427 SE 244th St<br>Kent, WA 98030</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Covington WA</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Help spread whistles in our community to protect against ICE. Whistles have been used successfully in Minneapolis, Los Angeles, Chicago, and Charlotte.

Why Whistles? -Instant alert system -Simple, cheap, effective -Noise = visibility -Turns silence into community action -Warns others when ICE is in the area, so vulnerable people can get to safety and everyone else can come help -Together, we keep our communities safe.

Participants will make and take whistle kits to be shared throughout our community.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899971/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
