        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Protest Every Monday in Brea</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 3, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 2:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Busiest Intersection in Brea<br>Imperial Highway &amp; State College Boulevard<br>Brea, CA 92821</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>## Join INDIVISIBLE CA-45 in Brea for a high visibility **PEACEFUL protest**
## Monday March 2 will be the **One Year Anniversary** of our weekly protests

#### We will rally on every corner of the intersection of Imperial Highway and State College Boulevard in Brea, CA 92821. During rush hour, many thousands of cars will be passing by.

### RAIN CANCELS - Rain on the windshield and on the road and dark of night is a dangerous combination at the busiest intersection in Brea.

Some new safety guidelines starting November 3rd:
1.	 Do not cross streets unless absolutely necessary.  Select a corner for the rally and stay there.  (This is for your safety, as when it is dark drivers cannot see you as well. All of our close-calls have been with people crossing the street.)
2.	Remain behind the tape placed along the curb.
3.	For your signs to be more easily seen and read – please use white posters with black or dark lettering. (The artwork is pretty, but more difficult to see in the dark!)
4.	Try to stay in well lit areas.  Wear light colored clothing.

### Protest for Democracy, the Rule Of Law, and **FREEDOM OF SPEECH**

## Protest against the brutality of ICE !!!

### Bring your signs

### Bring your flags.

## BRING YOUR COSTUME!

# Please be safe!

**DO NOT PARK anywhere in the shopping area on the southwest corner of Imperial and State College.** Southeast and Northeast corners are best.

This a local Indivisible event!
**A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to _DE-ESCALATE_ any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.**</p>
