    <Placemark>
        <name>ICE Out Of Home Depot - Otay Mesa</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Out Of Home Depot - Otay Mesa</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Otay Mesa Home Depot<br>950 Dennery Rd<br>San Diego, CA 92154</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Across the country, ICE agents continue to target immigrants in and around Home Depot stores - workers, customers, and surrounding communities. 

These raids are chaotic, violent, and sometimes deadly.

Through its silence and inaction, Home Depot is allowing its properties to become staging grounds for enforcement activity. Each incident deepens fear and instability in our neighborhoods. 

Our nationwide actions have shown that people are paying attention - and now we must keep up the pressure.

These atrocities are happening on Home Depot’s watch. When a corporation allows its spaces to be used in ways that endanger vulnerable communities and does nothing to intervene, silence becomes complicity.

As a major U.S. company in ALL of our communities, that says it wants to be a part of our communities, we expect more from Home Depot.  

** 

Today, in San Diego County, Home Depot refuses to provide laborers with a safe place to seek work, denying them basic dignity and respect.  And now, it has become an unsafe place for anyone on their property- including day laborers, and customers and their own neighbors.  

** 

Saturday, February 28th, San Diegans will take part in a coordinated action at Home Depot stores across San Diego county. 

Participants will gather outside their local Home Depot for brief chants before entering the store calmly.  While carrying signs and engaging respectfully with customers and employees, a demand letter will be delivered to store management during the action. 

Each store will have a designated leader, and actions may vary slightly by location.  

This is a collective, peaceful action to stand up for our neighbors and show the strength of community solidarity.   

Join us and make your voice count.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909418/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
