<h3>&quot;We Are All Protesters&quot; Live Protest Music Event - Benefits The ACLU</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 10:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Soap Factory<br>2995 Commercial St<br>San Diego, CA 92113</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Come and join like-minded peaceful activists as many of San Diego&apos;s finest musicians and bands perform live protest music.

The Soap Factory in Logan Heights hosts the first &quot;We Are All Protesters&quot; event , featuring live music, live protest poster creations, and more.

Proceeds from the event support the ACLU of San Diego &amp; Imperial Counties and a number of community outreach organizations.

Let&apos;s stop ICE!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
