        <name>Tell DHS We Stand With Our Neighbors</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Tell DHS We Stand With Our Neighbors</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 12:00 AM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Department of Homeland Security<br>12500 Tukwila International Blvd<br>Tukwila, WA 98168</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Southend Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join a group of fired up but peaceful freedom fighters to greet the agents and staff pulling out of the DHS parking lot with signage, presence, and voices. These purveyors of so much suffering in our community will be wrapping up their day of separating families, forcing school lock downs, deporting women and children to dangerous countries they&apos;ve never been, and terrorizing communities of color.

We will be doing so lawfully and peacefully (but not quietly) on the public sidewalk outside of the Department of Homeland Security in Tukwila.

We will be reminding these people of their sworn oath to the U.S. Constitution and to the American people, and NOT to the white nationalist, lawless, corrupt strongman in the White House. We will also make sure they know loud and clear that immigrants make our neighborhoods and communities better and stronger, and we will fight like hell to keep them here where they belong. 

No more abductions, no more murders, no more terror - ICE OUT NOW!

A core tenet of Indivisible is peaceful, non-violent resistance and we will abide by this at all actions we host or co-host.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/905192/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
