        <name>Protest New ICE Office Outside Sabey HQ</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Protest New ICE Office Outside Sabey HQ</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 12:30 AM UTC - 2:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Sabey Corporation HQ<br>12201 Tukwila International Blvd<br>Tukwila, WA 98168</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Southend Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join a broad coalition of freedom fighters for a protest outside Sabey Corporation&apos;s HQ, the secretive, privately-owned, Trump-supporting company looking to lease yet another large building to ICE/DHS to further empower its agenda of terror on our communities. 

READ BELOW FOR PARKING AND PUBLIC TRANSIT INFORMATION.

Our growing powerhouse coalition packing this protest includes Des Moines Indivisible, Evergreen Resistance, Federal Way Indivisible, Indivisible Auburn, Indivisible Covington, Indivisible Enumclaw, Indivisible Maple Valley, Indivisible Vashon, Kent Indivisible, Seattle Alliance Against Racist and Political Oppression, Seattle Democratic Socialists of America, Seattle Indivisible, South Seattle Indivisible, Southend Indivisible, Troublemakers, West Seattle Indivisible, and West Seattle Resist.

IF YOUR ORG WANTS TO JOIN THE COALITION please email southendindivisible@gmail.com.

BRIEF HISTORY: Sabey Corporation has long been a problem for our community and already leases a building to ICE/DHS just down the street at 12500 Tukwila Int. Blvd., which neighbors have been protesting for over a year. After bribing Trump with a $50,000 donation, they are now looking to add to their portfolio of terror by leasing Riverfront Technical Park to ICE, located at 2811 S 102nd St, Tukwila. 

SAFE / PEACEFUL / LAWFUL PRESENCE - A core tenet of Indivisible and our partner organizations is peaceful, lawful, non-violent resistance and we will abide by this at all rallies and protests we host or co-host (peaceful does not mean quiet!). If you plan to be any other way, please do not come. 

If you encounter a safety issue, please notify the Safety Team in the yellow vests right away.

WHAT WILL WE DO: We will stand, wave signs, and make noise on the limited public sidewalk in front of Sabey HQ and along the much longer sidewalks on both sides of the street along the adjacent street that is close to Sabey on the same block where DHS sits. We will do this with many cars passing by during rush hour to demand Sabey immediately stop leasing buildings to those kidnappings our neighbors, separating families, and terrorizing our community. COME EARLY If you want to be standing directly in front of Sabey Corporation on the limited public sidewalk on that stretch.

WHAT TO BRING: Bring your voices, your feet, your bullhorns, your drums, and your eye-popping, powerful signs. Also bring people to pack this and make a statement that can&apos;t be ignored - your family, friends, neighbors, co-workers, and more. And no worries if you don&apos;t have a sign - we&apos;ll have pre-made signs and materials for making new ones on the spot.

HOW TO GET THERE: 

With limited free parking that involves a walk, it is highly advised to take public transportation, Uber/Lyft/taxi, or carpool. 

BUS / TRAIN - Metro #124 is your bus as it runs all along Tukwila International Blvd. You may also take light rail to the Tukwila Light Rail Station, where you can catch a #124 heading north along Tukwila International Blvd. Plug in your trip here:  https://tripplanner.kingcounty.gov/#/app/tripplanning

PARKING: 

FREE RESIDENTIAL STREET PARKING - There is parking a 10 minute walk to Sabey that involves a flight of stairs on one side and going briefly up a hill on the other while Tukwila International Blvd itself is fairly flat.

On one side of Tukwila International Blvd (same side as Sabey), plug in your GPS the corner of 33rd Pl S &amp; S 130th St and work your way to park to that area. It&apos;s a little tricky and involves driving around to get up to it from other streets. You would then walk downhill from where you parked to Tukwila International Blvd and take a short flight of stairs which ends right where a 1-800-GOT JUNK business is located, and then walk northward along Tukwila International Blvd.

On the other side of Tukwila International Blvd (same side as DHS) you park around S 130th St &amp; 30th Ave S, then work your way up a short hill to Tukwila International Blvd and walk northward.

Be warned however that there are no sidewalks in either of those residential areas, and while parking in much of the area is fine, look around you to make sure you aren&apos;t sticking too far out in the street, you aren&apos;t blocking a driveway, or aren&apos;t parking where this is a &quot;no parking&quot; sign.

Paid parking, including ADA parking, is available in the DHS lot. If you have a choice, for obvious reasons, try to avoid that if possible. We still wanted those with limited mobility to be aware of this option if public transportation and Uber/Lyft/taxi is not.   

Join us to demand these corporate billionaires immediately stop empowering ICE terror!

In the meantime, give the Sabey C-Suite a little heat at their publicly available phone numbers and emails:

Send a letter in 3 minutes: 
https://actionnetwork.org/letters/sabey-corporation-stop-collaborating-with-ice

Contact Sabey directly: 
206-281-8700
https://sabey.com/contact-us

Ideas for text:
&quot;Do Not Lease Riverfront to ICE&quot;

&quot;Stop Supporting ICE Terror&quot;

&quot;Shame On You For Harming Our Community&quot;

Contact Executives:

Joe Sabey
President, Chief Commercial Officer AND Mayor of Hunts Point, WA
joes@sabey.com
mayor@huntspoint-wa.gov

Clete Casper 
206-277-5229
cletec@sabey.com

See the executives on Sabey&apos;s public website here: https://sabey.com/about/our-team</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/907349/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
