        <name>In-Person Lunchtime Meeting w/ Sen. Cantwell&apos;s Staff</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>In-Person Lunchtime Meeting w/ Sen. Cantwell&apos;s Staff</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, September 9, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 8:45 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Federal Office Building<br><br>Seattle, WA 98104</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Seattle Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p># Join Seattle Indivisible for a Critical Discussion with Senator Cantwell&apos;s Staff

Join Seattle Indivisible for an engaging Zoom discussion and Q&amp;A session with staff from Senator Maria Cantwell&apos;s office. As we navigate a complex political landscape in 2025, several key issues demand our attention:

Key Issues in 2026
🧊 Paramilitary Forces Attacking Immigrants and our Cities
ICE and CPB waging illegal, violent campaigns against immigrants and Black and brown people. 


🏛️ Constitutional Concerns
The ongoing failure of institutions to protect our rights and programs established by Congress have raised serious questions about the erosion of democratic principles.

💰 Economic Uncertainty
The imposition of a federal spending freeze has led to confusion and legal challenges, impacting various programs and contributing to fiscal instability.

⚖️ Social Equity
Policies targeting marginalized communities, including restrictions on transgender rights and potential cuts to social safety nets, underscore the ongoing struggle for social justice.

Senator Cantwell has been a vocal advocate for protecting democratic institutions, promoting economic stability, and advancing social equity. This session offers a unique opportunity to engage directly with her staff on these pressing issues.

📢 Your participation is crucial in voicing concerns and influencing decisions that impact our community.

We look forward to your active involvement in shaping the future of our state and nation!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/891165/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
