        <name>National call.  ICE OUT OF OUR COMMUNITIES.</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>National call.  ICE OUT OF OUR COMMUNITIES.</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, March 6, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> National Day Laborer Organizing Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for the next ICE Out of Our Communities national call. 

Friday March 6 at 1pm pst // 4pm est.  

For weeks, the popular cry nationwide has been clear:  ICE OUT NOW.  And Trump and ICE have been forced to take steps - or at least to pretend to take steps - to back out of MN.  We know its not true.  Dont be fooled, Ice hasn&apos;t gone anywhere.   We know that ICE is still present in MN and in so many of our communities.  More than than, we know ICE is planning to expand - both by hiring more agents and by colluding with local police and sheriffs - without the public noticing.    

Today, we must take action to ensure that we don&apos;t lose momentum in the fight to get ICE OUT.  

Call to action - 
* Ensure your locality is SAYING NO - no funds, no collaboration, no collusion
* Example - citizen shot by ice cover -up … 

* What to do?   Find your people… Cut ties, Enact policies , Corporate

people have mobilized and shown up- the tide is turning, and Ice has been exposed for what it is - a very real threat to our safety and civic life.  

This effort builds on years of organizing led by immigrant communities nationwide — from the fight against 287g contracts to the sanctuary victories that have proven local action works. Cities and states that say NO to ICE are a critical bulwark against mass deportations and the erosion of civil rights.

There is much that we can do locally. And there is much that our elected officials can do — if we demand courage and leadership. Join us!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/911158/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
