        <name>Neighborhood Readiness for ICE - Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Neighborhood Readiness for ICE - Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 8:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Bellingham Unitarian Fellowship<br>1207 Ellsworth St<br>Bellingham, WA 98225</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Bellingham</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Getting the community ready for ICE resistance.

We are seeing increasing ICE overreach and military surges in blue cities around the country along with increasing violence and virtually no accountability. Activists and protestors are being injured, detained and murdered. The most effective counteraction to this has been neighborhood by neighborhood organization and pushback by people just like you and me. The message from every city affected by an ICE surge has been that they wish that they had started preparing earlier. 
If you want to support your neighbors and document when something wrong is going down and you’d like to help prepare your neighbors (or your book club or faith group or friends and family) to do the same, then this class if for you. 
You will learn:
	Your legal rights when documenting
	How to document effectively
	Role of whistles
	De-escalation strategies…and more
You will also get a chance to practice your new skills and go home with information packets to help you take action when needed and to inform others. 
This administration wants us isolated and afraid because it gives them power. The antidote to that is community, because in community we have the power.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908570/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
