    <Placemark>
        <name>National Day of Lobbying 2: ICR - With Congressional Candidate Zeva Rosenbaum (OR-05)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>National Day of Lobbying 2: ICR - With Congressional Candidate Zeva Rosenbaum (OR-05)</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 9, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 9:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Janelle Bynum&apos;s Oregon City District Office<br>502 7th St Suite 203<br>Oregon City, OR 97045</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> 50501Missouri</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Democracy does not defend itself; it requires the active participation of the people. This moment demands something very visible, direct, and powerful: constituents showing up at congressional district offices, where staff rarely, if ever, engage with constituents.

On 2.17, constituents from across all 50 states went into at least 110 in-district offices of US Representatives to talk about impeaching Trump and abolishing ICE. Some offices locked their doors and appeared visibly shaken (e.g., Nancy Mace); others sat down and had tough conversations with constituents. Across most offices – a common theme emerged: we don’t want to have to see you and have this discussion again.

So, on 3.9 – we’re going back! Impeachment is not optional. It is the remedy mandated by the Constitution. Likewise, Congress holds the power to de-fund and abolish ICE. They aren’t acting because they do not have the political will to do so. So we will lend them some more of ours. (The follow-up is when it starts to become really uncomfortable for the offices.)

WHO/WHEN:

On Monday, 3/9, FLARE USA, Citizens&apos; Impeachment, Sons of Liberty, state chapters of 50501, progressive candidates like Zeva Rosenbaum, and many other concerned citizens will join together in leading constituents into the local/in-district offices of all 435 US House Representatives to demand impeachment and the abolishment of ICE.

WHERE:

Janelle Bynum’s local office in Oregon City. Across the street from City Hall in the Creative Building. 

Find your US Representative&apos;s home district office(s) here: https://national-day-of-lobbying.netlify.app/ 

Additional notes:

Please see our full attendee guide from 2.17 at https://tinyurl.com/lobby217guide. Note that a new guide is being developed and will be provided very soon.

Hosts and attendees are encouraged to watch the training webinar from 2.17 at https://flareusa.link/217masscall. 

Make sure to join the Impeachment Coalition for additional messaging and to connect with other organizers. You can join here: https://citizensimpeachment.com/the-impeachment-coalition/

All actions under this banner are committed to lawful, non-violent action and no civil disobedience. 

By registering for the event, you are agreeing that event partners may receive your contact information and communicate with you about related activities. 

Please contact FLARE USA (events@flareusa.org) with any questions!</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908953/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
