        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Stitch to Resist Cast-on</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Friday, February 27, 2026 at 2:30 AM UTC - 4:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>300 W 8th St<br>Vancouver, WA 98660</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Greater Vancouver</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>ATTENTION: Group size is limited to 20. You must register to attend.

All knitters and crocheters interested in creating Melt the ICE hats are welcome to join Stitch to Resist!
 The Stitch to Resist fiber craft circle will meet every Thursday through March 26th to create a large number of Melt the ICE hats to be given away to protesters to wear on No Kings Day—and every day!

The color for No Kings Day is yellow, however, wearing of these red caps creates solidarity with the folks in Minnesota who have adopted this historical connection with the Norwegian resistance during WWII.


Bring your own yarn and needles or use the donated yarn available. Please purchase pattern $5 on Ravelry. Pattern is called Melt the ICE hat by Paul Neary. Proceeds go to immigrant aid groups. If you have a snack to share, bring it!

For further information, or if you would like to donate yarn or cash, please contact Joy Robertson-Maciel at jrobertsonmaciel@gmail.com.</p>
