<h3>STAND UP AND SPEAK OUT</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 7, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Jefferson Street &amp; East Sims Way<br>Port Townsend, WA 98368</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We bring our signs, friends and noisemakers to our customary Saturday sign waving area along East Sims Way in Port Townsend. We have plenty of MAGA misdeeds to vent about: No Kings, No Dictators, Block Ice, Stop the Corruption, etc. 
Organized by Indivisible Port Townsend. Please bring a shelf-stable donation for the Jefferson County Food Bank too. They will be on hand to collect any nonperishable and nonexpired food items. They need our help in these troubled times. We can do this for our community at the same time we raise our signs and voices.

This a local Indivisible event!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
