        <name>Canby Day Without an Immigrant/Día sin inmigrante</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Canby Day Without an Immigrant/Día sin inmigrante</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 16, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Along 99E between S Grant St and S Ivy St in Canby, OR<br>Canby, OR 97013</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for a sign waving event to show support for the vulnerable members of our community. Let them know they are not alone.

Location: along 99E between S Ivy St and S Grant St in Canby, OR. Time: Monday, March 16th, 2026 from 12pm-2pm.

Parking available at Zoar Lutheran Church 190 SW 3rd Ave, Canby, OR 97013.

Endorsed by Bridging Cultures/Puentes Entre Culturas.

From PCUN (Oregon&apos;s Farmworker Union): Immigrant workers are the backbone of Oregon&apos;s most important sectors. We came here following the American dream, and to build a better life for our families. We work the jobs nobody else will do. They are backbreaking, low-paid, and sometimes dangerous. We helped make this country the richest country in the world. 

We&apos;re not criminals, we&apos;re families, workers, PEOPLE!

We have seen an overwhelming increase in ICE and Border Patrol in our communities, terrorizing our children, destabilizing our local business, harming our community. We have something Trump and his cronies want, our labor, our money, our time.

No work. No shopping. No school. Join our cause!

Our goal is to get ICE Out of our barrios by building solidarity amongst allies and immigrant workers. We need other sectors to stand up against gestapo immigration enforcement, and find real solutions to our broken immigration system.

What Happens on a Day Without An Immigrant? We&apos;re asking YOU to take the day off of work, and NOT participate economically. A Day Without An Immigrant is for all sectors of the economy. Thanks for your support!

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/910564/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
