        <name>Navigating Community Safety Around ICE</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Navigating Community Safety Around ICE</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 9:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Beaverton City Library<br>12375 SW 5th St<br>Beaverton, OR 97005</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We will be continuing our discussion over safety concerns as we discuss navigating community safety around ICE. Beaverton Mayor Lacey Beaty, city council members, and county officials will keep us up to date on the role they are playing and answer questions. 
  As ICE continues its siege around the country, concern for neighbors and those speaking out continues to climb. And as illegal arrests, detainments, and deportations continue and people continue to get injured and killed by ICE agents, Indivisible advocates for an end to brutal enforcement and an end to the violence and abuse. As a sanctuary state, we support the protection of our communities by our elected leaders and state and local law enforcement. 
  There will be time for Q and A with our speakers. 

*A core principle behind all Indivisible events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any
potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.</p>
