        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Food and Diaper Drive for Immigrant Families</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 6:00 PM UTC - 9:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Beaverton City Park by the Farmer&apos;s Market<br>12500 SW 4th St<br>Beaverton, OR 97005</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Stand Strong Beaverton</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join us for the final weekend of our Food and Diaper Drive to help immigrant families affected by ICE. Please bring nonperishable foods, diapers and formula. What we collect will go to Hands Off Portland and they will organize the safe delivery. 

This event also publicizes the next No Kings rally on March 28th from 2 to 4 p.m. in Beaverton City Park. We will all wear red, white and blue on that day.  Mini flags will be distributed. This event is brought to you by Stand Strong Beaverton, a local Indivisible group.</p>
