    <Placemark>
        <name>No Kings Day Woodburn! Stand Up for Our Community</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No Kings Day Woodburn! Stand Up for Our Community</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 7:00 PM UTC - 10:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Woodburn Transit Center by I-5, on Hwy 214<br>2900 Tom Tennant Dr<br>Woodburn, OR 97071</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Woodburn Hubbard Aurora Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We&apos;re Woodburn Indivisible, working hard to stop the damage ICE is doing to our small town-- and we need you to help us be able to help Woodburn. * Email WoodburnIndivisible@Yahoo.com * to let us know you will stand strong with us on No King&apos;s Day Woodburn, 12 Noon to 3 PM on March 28, 2026. We start at the Transit Center and expand towards Hwy 99. Or, just show up. We&apos;ll even provide the sign &amp; camaraderie.

Estimates are that nearly 100 people have been disappeared from Woodburn. No other Oregon city has been hit as hard as our little town. That&apos;s why it&apos;s so important that you be at the Transit Center to show the world that Woodburn is made of strong stuff &amp; that we&apos;re going to keep working to help our vulnerable neighbors stay safe from being hunted and captured, then disappeared. 

You may even decide that you want to be a permanent part of our warm, determined, committed Indivisible chapter that meets weekly to chart a course to help stop the destruction ICE has caused in Woodburn. * Email WoodburnIndivisible@Yahoo.com * for details on how to become part of our friendly, dedicated team.

The reality is that our at-risk neighbors are going hungry; they&apos;re missing school and work; losing family members; and trying to stay alive without medicine and needed health care. We have children who no longer have their parents. So, what could be more important on a Saturday than standing with Woodburn Indivisible to demand that ICE stop terrorizing our residents, smashing their vehicle windows and violently dragging them  from their homes and cars? As you know, silence is complicity. That&apos;s why you&apos;re reading this, because you know what you should do, and must do.

If you&apos;ve been doom scrolling, use that time to discover the fulfillment and contentment that we found-- that can only come from finally doing the right thing. You came to this page for a reason. You&apos;ve done the hard part. The easy part is to do the right thing for yourself and our neighbors who are being hunted, captured and jailed in filthy, overcrowded prison camps. Just show up or email * WoodburnIndivisible@Yahoo.com * to tell us you&apos;ll stand with us to demand an end to the tyranny, brutal assaults and cruel kidnappings that leave children without parents. We&apos;ll welcome you into our family of merry protesters working hard to stop the tyranny and vicious cruelty that is devastating Woodburn. Join our team. We need you.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/907756/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
