        <name>MIGRA WATCH Class Woodburn *DATE, PLACE, TIME PROVIDED AFTER REGISTERING*</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>MIGRA WATCH Class Woodburn *DATE, PLACE, TIME PROVIDED AFTER REGISTERING*</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, February 25, 2026 at 11:30 AM UTC - 12:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>2900 Tom Tennant Dr- EMAIL FOR ACTUAL CLASS LOCATION<br>Woodburn, OR 97071</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Woodburn Hubbard Aurora Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Migra Watch is the class that teaches you in detail how to spot &amp; report ICE, relay incidents &amp; suspicions. *Email WoodburnIndivisible@Yahoo.com for date, time, details.* 

This class is kind of &quot;How to Be a Useful, Competent Activist 101&quot; and should be a &quot;mandatory&quot; pre-requisitie for everyone who is trying to help protect vulnerable neighbors. Learn: How to identify incidents, exactly how to report them, what to do, what not to do-- and how you can provide lots of help without getting off your couch. You will also learn how to use Signal from your couch or in the community to provide direct help. Whatever your level of risk, you will learn tasks that you can do to make sure abducted people are identified and provided help, and that their vehicle and belongings are looked after, not left to be vandalized. If you care about the devastation ICE is causing, sign up for this in-person class. These classes sometimes fill so sign up now and location, date &amp; time will be provided to you. 

Sponsored by Immanuel Lutheran Church &amp; Woodburn Indivisible. *Email WoodburnIndivisible@Yahoo.com for date, time, details.*</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/904788/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
