        <name>ALL ARE WELCOME. A VIGIL FOR REMEBRANCE, PEACE AND COMMUNITY IN FOLSOM</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ALL ARE WELCOME. A VIGIL FOR REMEBRANCE, PEACE AND COMMUNITY IN FOLSOM</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 2, 2026 at 2:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Lembi Park Pavilion<br>1302 Riley St<br>Folsom, CA 95630</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> California Democratic Party</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>We invite our community to gather for a solemn vigil honoring the lives of those who have died in the custody or under the actions of ICE and CBP. This gathering is a space for collective mourning, reflection, and solidarity with families and communities who continue to seek justice and accountability.

Together, we will remember the individuals whose lives were lost, speak their names, and reaffirm our commitment to dignity and human rights for all. Candles and space for reflection will be provided.

All are welcome to join in this moment of remembrance and support.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/910573/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
