        <name>A Vigil and Procession for the Dead and Disappeared by ICE</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>A Vigil and Procession for the Dead and Disappeared by ICE</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, March 17, 2026 at 1:00 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Oregon State Capitol<br>900 Court St NE<br>Salem, OR 97301</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Salem Region Indivisible</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>A vigil and candlelight procession for the dead and disappeared by ICE, in solidarity with &quot;A Day Without Immigrants.&quot;

Please wear mourning clothing, bring candles and ofrenda* offerings.

Vigilia y Procesión en honor a los desaparecidos y muertos en manos de ICE.
Por favor usen ropa de luto, traigan velas, y ofrendas.

Capitol Mall Plaza
900 Court St, NE Salem  
Lunes, 16 de Marzo, 6-8pm

*Ofrenda, meaning &quot;offering&quot; in Spanish, is a traditional altar built to welcome the spirits of family members and friends during their annual visit on Día de los Muertos. However, honoring ancestors or deceased loved ones is a personal expression of love, not strictly limited by the calendar.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908845/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
