        <name>ICE Watch: Stockton Community Check-In Booth</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ICE Watch: Stockton Community Check-In Booth</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, February 24, 2026 at 8:00 AM UTC - 6:59 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> 50501 SoCal</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>### Did you know that there&apos;s an ICE facility in Stockton? Our neighbors are being kidnapped and taken to be processed, transferred, and deported with no reason or due process.

### So what can you do? 
### Sign up to volunteer with the Stockton Community Check-in Booth (CCIB)! The CCIB is a permanent, community-operated support station that:

- ### Connects with community members to monitor if they are checking in and out of their ICE appointments safely
- ### Connects community members and families to available legal aid and support
- ### Monitors ICE activity
- ### is part of the greater ICE watch effort in Northern and Central California

### Visit this link to sign up for a shift: www.tinyurl.com/ICEWatch209
### Do not register directly on Mobilize, use the link above.
#
### Please note this is not a 50501 Modesto led action. We provide this listing in solidarity with a community led effort that is not associated with any particular group.</p>
