        <name>Melt the ICE: Bay Area Against Detention Camps</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Melt the ICE: Bay Area Against Detention Camps</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 10:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Gateway Plaza<br>790 W El Camino Real<br>Mountain View, CA 94040</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> It&apos;s Blue Turn</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Stand up against ICE detention centers on the National Day of Action!

It’s time to mobilize coordinated action to end detention centers now! This is about all of us: will you defend your community and stand up for what is right? We can win, but we must slow, disrupt, and corrode every piece of the ICE apparatus of state terror. It is time to shut down the detention camps and open the cages!

This is also an opportunity to protest Trump’s other power grabs, from military actions to revenge prosecutions to inflationary tariffs.

We will gather peacefully on the corner of Castro &amp; El Camino. Bring your anti-ICE signs. We&apos;ll be distributing information about how to fight ICE terror. See you there!

**Organized by It&apos;s Blue Turn Indivisible and Mountain View Voices for Peace and Justice**</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/908135/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
