        <name>No Kings 3: Peninsula Out In Force</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>No Kings 3: Peninsula Out In Force</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 9:00 PM UTC - 11:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Peninsula<br><br>Mountain View, CA 94040</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> It&apos;s Blue Turn</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>On March 28, people from across the Peninsula will gather along El Camino Real to celebrate the third No Kings Day and to stand up to the MAGA administration: illegal ICE actions, taking health care from millions to give tax breaks to billionaires, stripping women of control over their own bodies, protecting abusers—the list goes on. Courage is contagious. As we stand together in public, we help build the power we need to take back our country.

El Camino Real is also known as “the King’s Highway.” But on this day, thousands of us will turn the street into the **No Kings Highway**. Multiple events will take place from Sunnyvale up to San Mateo, all between **2:00 PM and 4:00 PM**.

Here in Palo Alto, we are planning an event that will combine **street protest** with **community-building activities** that celebrate our rights as Americans.  

**The details will be coming soon, so please RSVP to be notified.**

- [Volunteer for the event](https://forms.gle/kNY1LAsSTSqz39w5A)  
- [See all coalition events on the Peninsula](https://www.indivisiblepeninsulabayarea.org/)  

*A core principle behind all our events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.*</p>
