        <name>Peace Center Whistlemania</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Peace Center Whistlemania</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, February 28, 2026 at 1:30 AM UTC - 3:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Monterey Peace and Justice Center<br>1364 Fremont Boulevard<br>Seaside, CA 93955</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Monterey Bay</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>The Monterey Peace and Justice Center and the Peace Coalition of Monterey County are partnering with Indivisible Monterey&apos;s WhistleSTOP Campaign to host a Whistlemania in Seaside on Friday, February 27, from 5:30pm to 7pm. 

The event, which is free and open to all, gathers volunteers to assemble whistle kits for local community members to alert their neighbors when ICE is nearby. Join us! All ages welcome.

The WhistleSTOP Campaign is inspired by the collective action of thousands of community members in Minneapolis, Chicago, Los Angeles, Charlotte and elsewhere who have been using whistles to alert their friends and neighbors when ICE is nearby and/or abducting someone.

By literally blowing the whistle on ICE we encourage others to gather and protect community members. Be loud and gather a crowd!

The WhistleSTOP Campaign has a goal of providing 100,000 whistles to Monterey County residents to help them alert others when ICE is near.

You can also contribute to this event by making a financial gift that will help us buy more whistles. Donate online here: https://www.paypal.com/ncp/payment/5CLQEAHK5PTCJ</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/902619/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
