        <name>States Win SF (formerly Sister District Project): 2026 Monthly Citywide Zooms</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>States Win SF (formerly Sister District Project): 2026 Monthly Citywide Zooms</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 2:30 AM UTC - 3:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> States Win San Francisco</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join our States Win monthly Zooms to connect virtually as volunteers and neighbors, get the latest candidate/campaign news, hear about upcoming volunteer actions, and learn about the strategic importance of state legislatures as firewalls to Tr*mp&apos;s fascism, as we work to flip states from #redtoblue! 

Each month, we will share updates, important good news and be joined by a special guest speaker and/or highlight a special education topic key to our work.

Our first speaker of 2026 is a three-time adopted candidate, Virginia Delegate, Phil Hernandez (HD 94). Phil will join us to share updates on the numerous legislation he&apos;s sponsored and discuss efforts by the Democratic state government to rein in ICE and protect the freedoms of Virginians.

Past Speaker Series guests have included: Rob Bonta, Janet Napolitano, David Pepper, and Danica Roem.

We host virtual events on **Zoom the first Tuesday** of each month; in-person **Happy Hours on the last Tuesday** of each month; and in-person **Postcard events** on alternating third Sunday afternoons and Monday evenings each month;  plus marches, parties, auctions and more!

Since 2016, we&apos;ve been building enduring progressive power in the states to improve people&apos;s lives by supporting over 185 state legislative candidates and community-based organizations led by people of color on the ground, like [Carolina Federation Fund, We are Down Home, Tennessee Immigrant &amp; Refugee Rights Coalition (TIRRC) and The Equity Alliance](https://secure.actblue.com/donate/sd016-nc-tn-sf?refcode=mobilize), who do critical grassroots work year round.

Last year, we won all 32 of our races—not only turning Virginia into a Democratic trifecta, but also flipping critical seats in Iowa and Mississippi to break GOP supermajorities. In Minnesota, we preserved Democratic control in a pivotal special election. 

In 2024, we flipped critical seats in the North Carolina House and the Wisconsin Senate, breaking GOP supermajorities. In Pennsylvania, we defended our hard-fought Democratic majority in the House, and in Minnesota, we preserved Democratic control in a pivotal special election. 

Before that, we helped to flip VA&apos;s House of Delegates blue, while also keeping a blue hold the State Senate, ensuring that 35 million women in the south didn&apos;t lose vital healthcare access from the ONLY southern state without an abortion ban.
 
In 2022, our volunteers supported 18 state legislative races in battleground states and ALL of our candidates won—including in Arizona and Nevada, where the candidates we supported directly were running (each chapter gets paired with two or more races each year).

To learn more about the impact and strategy of States Win in the lead up to the 2031 redistricting, visit [StatesWin.org] (https://stateswin.org/our-approach/#our-plan).</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/894050/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
