        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>NO KINGS Burlingame</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Saturday, March 28, 2026 at 4:00 PM UTC - 6:00 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Bayside Crossing Overpass/Bayside Park on Airport Blvd<br>1125 Airport Blvd.(parking)<br>Burlingame, CA 94010</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> No Kings</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>**We have the power and are claiming it together. No Thrones. No Crowns. No Kings.**

# High Visibility demonstration on Hwy 101 overpass

Bannering 101 is a group of concerned citizens who display banners on the pedestrian overpass in protest of Trump&apos;s authoritarian takeover of our country. Join us on the pedestrian overpass near Broadway to stand up for democracy freedom and humanity and No Kings!

### Location: 
Bayside Crossing Hwy 101 pedestrian overpass at Broadway


### Parking:
Easiest parking is on the east side near the baseball field at Bayside Park on Airport Blvd. Walk through the lot towards the hotel. There is a gate in the fence. Walk through the gate and turn right. The overpass will be on your left, just before you reach the Broadway intersection. 
  https://maps.app.goo.gl/UgSn1vGjK73c7jCx6

You can access the overpass on Rollins Rd. on the West side of Hwy101. However, parking is usually very limited. 
What began in 2025 as a single day of defiance has become a sustained national resistance to tyranny, spreading from small towns to city centers and across every community determined to defend democracy. Our peaceful movement is bigger than ever.

When our families are under attack and costs are pushing people to the brink, silence is not an option. We will defend ourselves and our communities against this administration’s unjust and cruel acts of violence.

On March 28th, rise up, take to the streets, and say it loud: no thrones, no crowns, no kings. We’re not watching history happen—we’re making it. Join us.



 We create and display large banners on highway overpasses in the Bay Area.  In Burlingame, we use the Bayside pedestrian overpass near Broadway. Associated groups use overpasses on  Hwys 1, 17, 80 and 85. In the last year, together we have reached an estimated seven million drivers .

### Our banners

We string fabric letters together to create our messages. We also make large painted fabric banners.  Some of our recent messages include:

-END ICE TERROR
-TELL SENATE NO $ 4 ICE
-JUSTICE 4 ICE VICTIMS
- FUND HEALTHCARE NOT WARFARE


Join us, and help fight back in solidarity, as if democracy depends upon it. IT DOES!!
We have the banners...we need YOU! Bring friends, music, noisemakers, signs etc... Small signs can not be read from the freeway but will be seen by anyone passing by on the overpass.

Contact us at bannering101@gmail.com if you would like to know more or get involved. Visit visibilitybrigade.com to learn more about other groups like ours all over the country. Join Indivisible San Mateo https://www.indivisiblesanmateo.com or Indivisible Mid Peninsula https://indivisiblemp.org to organize with  your community.



*A core principle behind all No Kings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.*</p>
