        <name>Science Matters Book Club, February</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Science Matters Book Club, February</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Thursday, February 26, 2026 at 3:00 AM UTC - 5:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>The Annex<br>247 S Alaska St<br>Palmer, AK 99645</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Mat-Su United for Progress Alaska</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p># 📚 Science Matters Book Club

## February Discussion  
**Featured Book:**  
*[The Only Woman in the Room](https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39971465-the-only-woman-in-the-room)* by Marie Benedict

Dive into a historical novel about Hedy Lamarr, the glamorous Hollywood actress who was also a brilliant scientist and inventor. This book reveals her groundbreaking work in frequency-hopping technology that helped revolutionize modern communication during World War II, despite being overlooked in history. 
**Co-Hosted by Science Matters Book Club and Mat-Su United for Progress**

## 📖 Upcoming Reads

- **March 25:** *The Icepick Surgeon* — Sam Kean  
- **April 22:** *Many Things Under a Rock: The Mysteries of Octopuses* — David Scheel  
- **May 27:** *Lab Girl* — Hope Jahren  

**All are welcome!**</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/878291/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
