<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Hawai‘i Statewide Network</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Kona Indivisible for a beach social and potluck gathering at Kahalu&apos;u Beach Park from 4 to 6:30 pm on Sunday, March 1st.

Fighting for democracy is hard work, so be sure to take some time to relax and recharge by joining other KIND activists for some food, drink, and conversation. We ask that you bring a dish to share, beverages for yourself, and a great attitude.

Food Drive: Let’s show support and solidarity for our cherished local migrant Latino community who have been intensely impacted by the illegal and cruel actions of Donald Trump. Let’s help ease the pain for migrants who have been displaced and traumatized by ICE on Hawai’i Island. We are all in this together! 

Food Drive, Preferred Items for Aloha Latinos: 
	(Please make sure items are not expired — mahalo for your support!)
* Dried or canned beans (pinto &amp; black) 
* White rice
* Spaghetti Pasta
* Pasta sauce
* La Moderna alphabet pasta (in Latino food section, in cellophane bags)
* Peanut butter
* Bread (shelf-stable)
