    <Placemark>
        <name>ROAD TO MAY DAY 2026</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>ROAD TO MAY DAY 2026</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Sunday, March 1, 2026 at 8:00 PM UTC - 1:00 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Sunrise Movement</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Road To May Day 2026 - Sunrise Phoenix Hub

This subcommittee of Sunrise Phoenix is responsible for developing and coordinating our hub’s contribution to the nationwide May Day mobilization for labor rights.

We know there is no path to real climate progress under an authoritarian government. If democracy erodes, so does any chance of passing  or enforcing bold, people-first climate policy.

Taking on authoritarianism means identifying and challenging the pillars that uphold it. Here in Arizona ( a border state with a long history of racist policies targeting immigrants ) we see immigrants once again being scapegoated for America’s economic struggles. We reject that lie. Immigrants are not the cause of rising costs, housing shortages, or corporate greed.

We call out corrupt governments that protect billionaire interests, devastate our planet, and separate families to maintain power.

That’s why Sunrise Phoenix is clear: ICE is not welcome here.

We’re working alongside organizations across the state while building Sunrise’s unique role in this moment. We welcome young people under 35 who are ready to LEAD organize, strategize, and mobilize for May 1st and beyond.

If you’re ready to build power and confront the systems holding this crisis in place, join us.


*PLEASE NOTE: the date and time are a place holder, we will contact you after you sign up to coordinate the best time that works for all sign ups to start meeting and working on this project. thank you.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909243/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
