        <name>The Block Is Hot: Surveillance Teach-In</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>The Block Is Hot: Surveillance Teach-In</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 4, 2026 at 11:30 PM UTC - 1:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Harriet’s Wildest Dreams</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>Join Harriet&apos;s Wildest Dreams, the Claudia Jones School for Political Education, and No Tech for Apartheid for a comprehensive teach-in and conversation on surveillance technologies, national legislation, historical context, and practical resistance.

Learn about how surveillance has evolved from COINTELPRO of the Civil Rights and Black Power Movements, evolved into the post-9/11 War on Terrorism, became the basis for ICE, and morphed into the heightening police state of today.

Our subject matter experts will dive into how the technology tested against Palestinians in Gaza are brought to the U.S. and used by MPD, DFS, and HSEMA right here in the District.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/903449/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
