        <name>Know Your Rights and Bystander Training</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Know Your Rights and Bystander Training</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Monday, March 9, 2026 at 11:00 PM UTC - 12:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Indivisible Lower Merion (PA)</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>As ICE has intensified its presence and actions in our community, Indivisible Lower Merion invites you to join a virtual Know Your Rights and Bystander training offered by seasoned presenters who have offered these sessions across the region.   

From Los Angeles to Chicago to Minneapolis,neighbors have shown what it looks like to care for and defend one another against the lawlessness and violence of DHS, ICE, and CBP. 

This Know Your Rights and Bystander training is about building that same coordination and courage in Philadelphia and the surrounding area. 

A variety of topics will be covered, including bearing moral witness and constitutional observation, your rights in public and private spaces, mutual aid, neighborhoodism, community signal chats, and other tactics we can deploy.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/909443/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
