        <name>Breakfast Briefing: Defending Our Neighbors – ICE Activity, Rights and the Fight for Civil Liberties</name>
        <description><![CDATA[
<h3>Breakfast Briefing: Defending Our Neighbors – ICE Activity, Rights and the Fight for Civil Liberties</h3>
<p><strong>When:</strong> Wednesday, March 18, 2026 at 12:30 PM UTC - 1:30 PM</p>
<p><strong>Where:</strong><br>Location not specified</p>
<p><strong>Organized by:</strong> Represent PA</p>
<p><strong>About:</strong></p><p>As immigration enforcement ramps up and civil liberties face renewed pressure, staying informed–and prepared–has never mattered more. 

On Wednesday, March 18 at 8:30 AM, join us for a timely Breakfast Briefing that meets this moment head-on. 

We’ll hear from Heidi Roux, Director of Immigrant Justice at The Welcome Project PA, who will share what’s being observed locally around ICE activity, clearly explain your rights as an observer and outline practical ways to support the most vulnerable members of our communities right now.

We’re also honored to be joined by Senator Maria Collett, who will discuss a resolution she introduced with Senator Jay Costa condemning unconstitutional use of force by federal immigration officers, as well as additional legislation she plans to introduce to confront growing threats to civil liberties.

This isn’t a passive briefing. It’s a space to get smart, ask questions and leave with clarity about what’s happening and how to respond, together.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mobilize.us/event/899887/" target="_blank">View Event on Mobilize.us</a></p>
<p><i>Data source: mobilize.us | Updated: 2026-02-25T07:04:10.471Z</i></p>
]]></description>
